2226 bool CombinerHelper::matchCombineFAbsOfFNeg(MachineInstr &MI,
2227  BuildFnTy &MatchInfo) {
2228  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_FABS && "Expected a G_FABS");
2229  Register Src = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
2230  Register NegSrc;
2231 
2232  if (!mi_match(Src, MRI, m_GFNeg(m_Reg(NegSrc))))
2233  return false;
2234 
2235  MatchInfo = [=, &MI](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
2236  Observer.changingInstr(MI);
2237  MI.getOperand(1).setReg(NegSrc);
2238  Observer.changedInstr(MI);
2239  };
2240  return true;
2241 }

2243 bool CombinerHelper::matchCombineTruncOfExt(
2244  MachineInstr &MI, std::pair<Register, unsigned> &MatchInfo) {
2245  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_TRUNC && "Expected a G_TRUNC");
2246  Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
2247  MachineInstr *SrcMI = MRI.getVRegDef(SrcReg);
2248  unsigned SrcOpc = SrcMI->getOpcode();
2249  if (SrcOpc == TargetOpcode::G_ANYEXT || SrcOpc == TargetOpcode::G_SEXT ||
2250  SrcOpc == TargetOpcode::G_ZEXT) {
2251  MatchInfo = std::make_pair(SrcMI->getOperand(1).getReg(), SrcOpc);
2252  return true;
2253  }
2254  return false;
2255 }
2256 
2257 void CombinerHelper::applyCombineTruncOfExt(
2258  MachineInstr &MI, std::pair<Register, unsigned> &MatchInfo) {
2259  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_TRUNC && "Expected a G_TRUNC");
2260  Register SrcReg = MatchInfo.first;
2261  unsigned SrcExtOp = MatchInfo.second;
2262  Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
2263  LLT SrcTy = MRI.getType(SrcReg);
2264  LLT DstTy = MRI.getType(DstReg);
2265  if (SrcTy == DstTy) {
2266  MI.eraseFromParent();
2267  replaceRegWith(MRI, DstReg, SrcReg);
2268  return;
2269  }
2270  Builder.setInstrAndDebugLoc(MI);
2271  if (SrcTy.getSizeInBits() < DstTy.getSizeInBits())
2272  Builder.buildInstr(SrcExtOp, {DstReg}, {SrcReg});
2273  else
2274  Builder.buildTrunc(DstReg, SrcReg);
2275  MI.eraseFromParent();
2276 }
2277 
2278 static LLT getMidVTForTruncRightShiftCombine(LLT ShiftTy, LLT TruncTy) {
2279  const unsigned ShiftSize = ShiftTy.getScalarSizeInBits();
2280  const unsigned TruncSize = TruncTy.getScalarSizeInBits();
2281 
2282  // ShiftTy > 32 > TruncTy -> 32
2283  if (ShiftSize > 32 && TruncSize < 32)
2284  return ShiftTy.changeElementSize(32);
2285 
2286  // TODO: We could also reduce to 16 bits, but that's more target-dependent.
2287  // Some targets like it, some don't, some only like it under certain
2288  // conditions/processor versions, etc.
2289  // A TL hook might be needed for this.
2290 
2291  // Don't combine
2292  return ShiftTy;
2293 }
2294 
2295 bool CombinerHelper::matchCombineTruncOfShift(
2296  MachineInstr &MI, std::pair<MachineInstr *, LLT> &MatchInfo) {
2297  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_TRUNC && "Expected a G_TRUNC");
2298  Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
2299  Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
2300 
2301  if (!MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(SrcReg))
2302  return false;
2303 
2304  LLT SrcTy = MRI.getType(SrcReg);
2305  LLT DstTy = MRI.getType(DstReg);
2306 
2307  MachineInstr *SrcMI = getDefIgnoringCopies(SrcReg, MRI);
2308  const auto &TL = getTargetLowering();
2309 
2310  LLT NewShiftTy;
2311  switch (SrcMI->getOpcode()) {
2312  default:
2313  return false;
2314  case TargetOpcode::G_SHL: {
2315  NewShiftTy = DstTy;
2316 
2317  // Make sure new shift amount is legal.
2318  KnownBits Known = KB->getKnownBits(SrcMI->getOperand(2).getReg());
2319  if (Known.getMaxValue().uge(NewShiftTy.getScalarSizeInBits()))
2320  return false;
2321  break;
2322  }
2323  case TargetOpcode::G_LSHR:
2324  case TargetOpcode::G_ASHR: {
2325  // For right shifts, we conservatively do not do the transform if the TRUNC
2326  // has any STORE users. The reason is that if we change the type of the
2327  // shift, we may break the truncstore combine.
2328  //
2329  // TODO: Fix truncstore combine to handle (trunc(lshr (trunc x), k)).
2330  for (auto &User : MRI.use_instructions(DstReg))
2331  if (User.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_STORE)
2332  return false;
2333 
2334  NewShiftTy = getMidVTForTruncRightShiftCombine(SrcTy, DstTy);
2335  if (NewShiftTy == SrcTy)
2336  return false;
2337 
2338  // Make sure we won't lose information by truncating the high bits.
2339  KnownBits Known = KB->getKnownBits(SrcMI->getOperand(2).getReg());
2340  if (Known.getMaxValue().ugt(NewShiftTy.getScalarSizeInBits() -
2341  DstTy.getScalarSizeInBits()))
2342  return false;
2343  break;
2344  }
2345  }
2346 
2347  if (!isLegalOrBeforeLegalizer(
2348  {SrcMI->getOpcode(),
2349  {NewShiftTy, TL.getPreferredShiftAmountTy(NewShiftTy)}}))
2350  return false;
2351 
2352  MatchInfo = std::make_pair(SrcMI, NewShiftTy);
2353  return true;
2354 }
2355 
2356 void CombinerHelper::applyCombineTruncOfShift(
2357  MachineInstr &MI, std::pair<MachineInstr *, LLT> &MatchInfo) {
2358  Builder.setInstrAndDebugLoc(MI);
2359 
2360  MachineInstr *ShiftMI = MatchInfo.first;
2361  LLT NewShiftTy = MatchInfo.second;
2362 
2363  Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
2364  LLT DstTy = MRI.getType(Dst);
2365 
2366  Register ShiftAmt = ShiftMI->getOperand(2).getReg();
2367  Register ShiftSrc = ShiftMI->getOperand(1).getReg();
2368  ShiftSrc = Builder.buildTrunc(NewShiftTy, ShiftSrc).getReg(0);
2369 
2370  Register NewShift =
2371  Builder
2372  .buildInstr(ShiftMI->getOpcode(), {NewShiftTy}, {ShiftSrc, ShiftAmt})
2373  .getReg(0);
2374 
2375  if (NewShiftTy == DstTy)
2376  replaceRegWith(MRI, Dst, NewShift);
2377  else
2378  Builder.buildTrunc(Dst, NewShift);
2379 
2380  eraseInst(MI);
2381 }

2443 bool CombinerHelper::matchEqualDefs(const MachineOperand &MOP1,
2444  const MachineOperand &MOP2) {
2445  if (!MOP1.isReg() || !MOP2.isReg())
2446  return false;
2447  auto InstAndDef1 = getDefSrcRegIgnoringCopies(MOP1.getReg(), MRI);
2448  if (!InstAndDef1)
2449  return false;
2450  auto InstAndDef2 = getDefSrcRegIgnoringCopies(MOP2.getReg(), MRI);
2451  if (!InstAndDef2)
2452  return false;
2453  MachineInstr *I1 = InstAndDef1->MI;
2454  MachineInstr *I2 = InstAndDef2->MI;
2455 
2456  // Handle a case like this:
2457  //
2458  // %0:_(s64), %1:_(s64) = G_UNMERGE_VALUES %2:_(<2 x s64>)
2459  //
2460  // Even though %0 and %1 are produced by the same instruction they are not
2461  // the same values.
2462  if (I1 == I2)
2463  return MOP1.getReg() == MOP2.getReg();
2464 
2465  // If we have an instruction which loads or stores, we can't guarantee that
2466  // it is identical.
2467  //
2468  // For example, we may have
2469  //
2470  // %x1 = G_LOAD %addr (load N from @somewhere)
2471  // ...
2472  // call @foo
2473  // ...
2474  // %x2 = G_LOAD %addr (load N from @somewhere)
2475  // ...
2476  // %or = G_OR %x1, %x2
2477  //
2478  // It's possible that @foo will modify whatever lives at the address we're
2479  // loading from. To be safe, let's just assume that all loads and stores
2480  // are different (unless we have something which is guaranteed to not
2481  // change.)
2482  if (I1->mayLoadOrStore() && !I1->isDereferenceableInvariantLoad())
2483  return false;
2484 
2485  // If both instructions are loads or stores, they are equal only if both
2486  // are dereferenceable invariant loads with the same number of bits.
2487  if (I1->mayLoadOrStore() && I2->mayLoadOrStore()) {
2488  GLoadStore *LS1 = dyn_cast<GLoadStore>(I1);
2489  GLoadStore *LS2 = dyn_cast<GLoadStore>(I2);
2490  if (!LS1 || !LS2)
2491  return false;
2492 
2493  if (!I2->isDereferenceableInvariantLoad() ||
2494  (LS1->getMemSizeInBits() != LS2->getMemSizeInBits()))
2495  return false;
2496  }
2497 
2498  // Check for physical registers on the instructions first to avoid cases
2499  // like this:
2500  //
2501  // %a = COPY $physreg
2502  // ...
2503  // SOMETHING implicit-def $physreg
2504  // ...
2505  // %b = COPY $physreg
2506  //
2507  // These copies are not equivalent.
2508  if (any_of(I1->uses(), [](const MachineOperand &MO) {
2509  return MO.isReg() && MO.getReg().isPhysical();
2510  })) {
2511  // Check if we have a case like this:
2512  //
2513  // %a = COPY $physreg
2514  // %b = COPY %a
2515  //
2516  // In this case, I1 and I2 will both be equal to %a = COPY $physreg.
2517  // From that, we know that they must have the same value, since they must
2518  // have come from the same COPY.
2519  return I1->isIdenticalTo(*I2);
2520  }
2521 
2522  // We don't have any physical registers, so we don't necessarily need the
2523  // same vreg defs.
2524  //
2525  // On the off-chance that there's some target instruction feeding into the
2526  // instruction, let's use produceSameValue instead of isIdenticalTo.
2527  if (Builder.getTII().produceSameValue(*I1, *I2, &MRI)) {
2528  // Handle instructions with multiple defs that produce same values. Values
2529  // are same for operands with same index.
2530  // %0:_(s8), %1:_(s8), %2:_(s8), %3:_(s8) = G_UNMERGE_VALUES %4:_(<4 x s8>)
2531  // %5:_(s8), %6:_(s8), %7:_(s8), %8:_(s8) = G_UNMERGE_VALUES %4:_(<4 x s8>)
2532  // I1 and I2 are different instructions but produce same values,
2533  // %1 and %6 are same, %1 and %7 are not the same value.
2534  return I1->findRegisterDefOperandIdx(InstAndDef1->Reg) ==
2535  I2->findRegisterDefOperandIdx(InstAndDef2->Reg);
2536  }
2537  return false;
2538 }
2539 
2540 bool CombinerHelper::matchConstantOp(const MachineOperand &MOP, int64_t C) {
2541  if (!MOP.isReg())
2542  return false;
2543  auto *MI = MRI.getVRegDef(MOP.getReg());
2544  auto MaybeCst = isConstantOrConstantSplatVector(*MI, MRI);
2545  return MaybeCst && MaybeCst->getBitWidth() <= 64 &&
2546  MaybeCst->getSExtValue() == C;
2547 }

2634 bool CombinerHelper::matchSimplifyAddToSub(
2635  MachineInstr &MI, std::tuple<Register, Register> &MatchInfo) {
2636  Register LHS = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
2637  Register RHS = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
2638  Register &NewLHS = std::get<0>(MatchInfo);
2639  Register &NewRHS = std::get<1>(MatchInfo);
2640 
2641  // Helper lambda to check for opportunities for
2642  // ((0-A) + B) -> B - A
2643  // (A + (0-B)) -> A - B
2644  auto CheckFold = [&](Register &MaybeSub, Register &MaybeNewLHS) {
2645  if (!mi_match(MaybeSub, MRI, m_Neg(m_Reg(NewRHS))))
2646  return false;
2647  NewLHS = MaybeNewLHS;
2648  return true;
2649  };
2650 
2651  return CheckFold(LHS, RHS) || CheckFold(RHS, LHS);
2652 }
2653 
2654 bool CombinerHelper::matchCombineInsertVecElts(
2655  MachineInstr &MI, SmallVectorImpl<Register> &MatchInfo) {
2656  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_INSERT_VECTOR_ELT &&
2657  "Invalid opcode");
2658  Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
2659  LLT DstTy = MRI.getType(DstReg);
2660  assert(DstTy.isVector() && "Invalid G_INSERT_VECTOR_ELT?");
2661  unsigned NumElts = DstTy.getNumElements();
2662  // If this MI is part of a sequence of insert_vec_elts, then
2663  // don't do the combine in the middle of the sequence.
2664  if (MRI.hasOneUse(DstReg) && MRI.use_instr_begin(DstReg)->getOpcode() ==
2665  TargetOpcode::G_INSERT_VECTOR_ELT)
2666  return false;
2667  MachineInstr *CurrInst = &MI;
2668  MachineInstr *TmpInst;
2669  int64_t IntImm;
2670  Register TmpReg;
2671  MatchInfo.resize(NumElts);
2672  while (mi_match(
2673  CurrInst->getOperand(0).getReg(), MRI,
2674  m_GInsertVecElt(m_MInstr(TmpInst), m_Reg(TmpReg), m_ICst(IntImm)))) {
2675  if (IntImm >= NumElts || IntImm < 0)
2676  return false;
2677  if (!MatchInfo[IntImm])
2678  MatchInfo[IntImm] = TmpReg;
2679  CurrInst = TmpInst;
2680  }
2681  // Variable index.
2682  if (CurrInst->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_INSERT_VECTOR_ELT)
2683  return false;
2684  if (TmpInst->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_BUILD_VECTOR) {
2685  for (unsigned I = 1; I < TmpInst->getNumOperands(); ++I) {
2686  if (!MatchInfo[I - 1].isValid())
2687  MatchInfo[I - 1] = TmpInst->getOperand(I).getReg();
2688  }
2689  return true;
2690  }
2691  // If we didn't end in a G_IMPLICIT_DEF, bail out.
2692  return TmpInst->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_IMPLICIT_DEF;
2693 }
2694 
2695 void CombinerHelper::applyCombineInsertVecElts(
2696  MachineInstr &MI, SmallVectorImpl<Register> &MatchInfo) {
2697  Builder.setInstr(MI);
2698  Register UndefReg;
2699  auto GetUndef = [&]() {
2700  if (UndefReg)
2701  return UndefReg;
2702  LLT DstTy = MRI.getType(MI.getOperand(0).getReg());
2703  UndefReg = Builder.buildUndef(DstTy.getScalarType()).getReg(0);
2704  return UndefReg;
2705  };
2706  for (unsigned I = 0; I < MatchInfo.size(); ++I) {
2707  if (!MatchInfo[I])
2708  MatchInfo[I] = GetUndef();
2709  }
2710  Builder.buildBuildVector(MI.getOperand(0).getReg(), MatchInfo);
2711  MI.eraseFromParent();
2712 }
2713 
2714 void CombinerHelper::applySimplifyAddToSub(
2715  MachineInstr &MI, std::tuple<Register, Register> &MatchInfo) {
2716  Builder.setInstr(MI);
2717  Register SubLHS, SubRHS;
2718  std::tie(SubLHS, SubRHS) = MatchInfo;
2719  Builder.buildSub(MI.getOperand(0).getReg(), SubLHS, SubRHS);
2720  MI.eraseFromParent();
2721 }
2722 
2723 bool CombinerHelper::matchHoistLogicOpWithSameOpcodeHands(
2724  MachineInstr &MI, InstructionStepsMatchInfo &MatchInfo) {
2725  // Matches: logic (hand x, ...), (hand y, ...) -> hand (logic x, y), ...
2726  //
2727  // Creates the new hand + logic instruction (but does not insert them.)
2728  //
2729  // On success, MatchInfo is populated with the new instructions. These are
2730  // inserted in applyHoistLogicOpWithSameOpcodeHands.
2731  unsigned LogicOpcode = MI.getOpcode();
2732  assert(LogicOpcode == TargetOpcode::G_AND ||
2733  LogicOpcode == TargetOpcode::G_OR ||
2734  LogicOpcode == TargetOpcode::G_XOR);
2735  MachineIRBuilder MIB(MI);
2736  Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
2737  Register LHSReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
2738  Register RHSReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
2739 
2740  // Don't recompute anything.
2741  if (!MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(LHSReg) || !MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(RHSReg))
2742  return false;
2743 
2744  // Make sure we have (hand x, ...), (hand y, ...)
2745  MachineInstr *LeftHandInst = getDefIgnoringCopies(LHSReg, MRI);
2746  MachineInstr *RightHandInst = getDefIgnoringCopies(RHSReg, MRI);
2747  if (!LeftHandInst || !RightHandInst)
2748  return false;
2749  unsigned HandOpcode = LeftHandInst->getOpcode();
2750  if (HandOpcode != RightHandInst->getOpcode())
2751  return false;
2752  if (!LeftHandInst->getOperand(1).isReg() ||
2753  !RightHandInst->getOperand(1).isReg())
2754  return false;
2755 
2756  // Make sure the types match up, and if we're doing this post-legalization,
2757  // we end up with legal types.
2758  Register X = LeftHandInst->getOperand(1).getReg();
2759  Register Y = RightHandInst->getOperand(1).getReg();
2760  LLT XTy = MRI.getType(X);
2761  LLT YTy = MRI.getType(Y);
2762  if (!XTy.isValid() || XTy != YTy)
2763  return false;
2764  if (!isLegalOrBeforeLegalizer({LogicOpcode, {XTy, YTy}}))
2765  return false;
2766 
2767  // Optional extra source register.
2768  Register ExtraHandOpSrcReg;
2769  switch (HandOpcode) {
2770  default:
2771  return false;
2772  case TargetOpcode::G_ANYEXT:
2773  case TargetOpcode::G_SEXT:
2774  case TargetOpcode::G_ZEXT: {
2775  // Match: logic (ext X), (ext Y) --> ext (logic X, Y)
2776  break;
2777  }
2778  case TargetOpcode::G_AND:
2779  case TargetOpcode::G_ASHR:
2780  case TargetOpcode::G_LSHR:
2781  case TargetOpcode::G_SHL: {
2782  // Match: logic (binop x, z), (binop y, z) -> binop (logic x, y), z
2783  MachineOperand &ZOp = LeftHandInst->getOperand(2);
2784  if (!matchEqualDefs(ZOp, RightHandInst->getOperand(2)))
2785  return false;
2786  ExtraHandOpSrcReg = ZOp.getReg();
2787  break;
2788  }
2789  }
2790 
2791  // Record the steps to build the new instructions.
2792  //
2793  // Steps to build (logic x, y)
2794  auto NewLogicDst = MRI.createGenericVirtualRegister(XTy);
2795  OperandBuildSteps LogicBuildSteps = {
2796  [=](MachineInstrBuilder &MIB) { MIB.addDef(NewLogicDst); },
2797  [=](MachineInstrBuilder &MIB) { MIB.addReg(X); },
2798  [=](MachineInstrBuilder &MIB) { MIB.addReg(Y); }};
2799  InstructionBuildSteps LogicSteps(LogicOpcode, LogicBuildSteps);
2800 
2801  // Steps to build hand (logic x, y), ...z
2802  OperandBuildSteps HandBuildSteps = {
2803  [=](MachineInstrBuilder &MIB) { MIB.addDef(Dst); },
2804  [=](MachineInstrBuilder &MIB) { MIB.addReg(NewLogicDst); }};
2805  if (ExtraHandOpSrcReg.isValid())
2806  HandBuildSteps.push_back(
2807  [=](MachineInstrBuilder &MIB) { MIB.addReg(ExtraHandOpSrcReg); });
2808  InstructionBuildSteps HandSteps(HandOpcode, HandBuildSteps);
2809 
2810  MatchInfo = InstructionStepsMatchInfo({LogicSteps, HandSteps});
2811  return true;
2812 }
2813 
2814 void CombinerHelper::applyBuildInstructionSteps(
2815  MachineInstr &MI, InstructionStepsMatchInfo &MatchInfo) {
2816  assert(MatchInfo.InstrsToBuild.size() &&
2817  "Expected at least one instr to build?");
2818  Builder.setInstr(MI);
2819  for (auto &InstrToBuild : MatchInfo.InstrsToBuild) {
2820  assert(InstrToBuild.Opcode && "Expected a valid opcode?");
2821  assert(InstrToBuild.OperandFns.size() && "Expected at least one operand?");
2822  MachineInstrBuilder Instr = Builder.buildInstr(InstrToBuild.Opcode);
2823  for (auto &OperandFn : InstrToBuild.OperandFns)
2824  OperandFn(Instr);
2825  }
2826  MI.eraseFromParent();
2827 }

2829 bool CombinerHelper::matchAshrShlToSextInreg(
2830  MachineInstr &MI, std::tuple<Register, int64_t> &MatchInfo) {
2831  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_ASHR);
2832  int64_t ShlCst, AshrCst;
2833  Register Src;
2834  if (!mi_match(MI.getOperand(0).getReg(), MRI,
2835  m_GAShr(m_GShl(m_Reg(Src), m_ICstOrSplat(ShlCst)),
2836  m_ICstOrSplat(AshrCst))))
2837  return false;
2838  if (ShlCst != AshrCst)
2839  return false;
2840  if (!isLegalOrBeforeLegalizer(
2841  {TargetOpcode::G_SEXT_INREG, {MRI.getType(Src)}}))
2842  return false;
2843  MatchInfo = std::make_tuple(Src, ShlCst);
2844  return true;
2845 }

2847 void CombinerHelper::applyAshShlToSextInreg(
2848  MachineInstr &MI, std::tuple<Register, int64_t> &MatchInfo) {
2849  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_ASHR);
2850  Register Src;
2851  int64_t ShiftAmt;
2852  std::tie(Src, ShiftAmt) = MatchInfo;
2853  unsigned Size = MRI.getType(Src).getScalarSizeInBits();
2854  Builder.setInstrAndDebugLoc(MI);
2855  Builder.buildSExtInReg(MI.getOperand(0).getReg(), Src, Size - ShiftAmt);
2856  MI.eraseFromParent();
2857 }

2859 /// and(and(x, C1), C2) -> C1&C2 ? and(x, C1&C2) : 0
2860 bool CombinerHelper::matchOverlappingAnd(
2861  MachineInstr &MI, std::function<void(MachineIRBuilder &)> &MatchInfo) {
2862  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_AND);
2863 
2864  Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
2865  LLT Ty = MRI.getType(Dst);
2866 
2867  Register R;
2868  int64_t C1;
2869  int64_t C2;
2870  if (!mi_match(
2871  Dst, MRI,
2872  m_GAnd(m_GAnd(m_Reg(R), m_ICst(C1)), m_ICst(C2))))
2873  return false;
2874 
2875  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
2876  if (C1 & C2) {
2877  B.buildAnd(Dst, R, B.buildConstant(Ty, C1 & C2));
2878  return;
2879  }
2880  auto Zero = B.buildConstant(Ty, 0);
2881  replaceRegWith(MRI, Dst, Zero->getOperand(0).getReg());
2882  };
2883  return true;
2884 }
2885 
2886 bool CombinerHelper::matchRedundantAnd(MachineInstr &MI,
2887  Register &Replacement) {
2888  // Given
2889  //
2890  // %y:_(sN) = G_SOMETHING
2891  // %x:_(sN) = G_SOMETHING
2892  // %res:_(sN) = G_AND %x, %y
2893  //
2894  // Eliminate the G_AND when it is known that x & y == x or x & y == y.
2895  //
2896  // Patterns like this can appear as a result of legalization. E.g.
2897  //
2898  // %cmp:_(s32) = G_ICMP intpred(pred), %x(s32), %y
2899  // %one:_(s32) = G_CONSTANT i32 1
2900  // %and:_(s32) = G_AND %cmp, %one
2901  //
2902  // In this case, G_ICMP only produces a single bit, so x & 1 == x.
2903  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_AND);
2904  if (!KB)
2905  return false;
2906 
2907  Register AndDst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
2908  Register LHS = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
2909  Register RHS = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
2910  KnownBits LHSBits = KB->getKnownBits(LHS);
2911  KnownBits RHSBits = KB->getKnownBits(RHS);
2912 
2913  // Check that x & Mask == x.
2914  // x & 1 == x, always
2915  // x & 0 == x, only if x is also 0
2916  // Meaning Mask has no effect if every bit is either one in Mask or zero in x.
2917  //
2918  // Check if we can replace AndDst with the LHS of the G_AND
2919  if (canReplaceReg(AndDst, LHS, MRI) &&
2920  (LHSBits.Zero | RHSBits.One).isAllOnes()) {
2921  Replacement = LHS;
2922  return true;
2923  }
2924 
2925  // Check if we can replace AndDst with the RHS of the G_AND
2926  if (canReplaceReg(AndDst, RHS, MRI) &&
2927  (LHSBits.One | RHSBits.Zero).isAllOnes()) {
2928  Replacement = RHS;
2929  return true;
2930  }
2931 
2932  return false;
2933 }
2934 
2935 bool CombinerHelper::matchRedundantOr(MachineInstr &MI, Register &Replacement) {
2936  // Given
2937  //
2938  // %y:_(sN) = G_SOMETHING
2939  // %x:_(sN) = G_SOMETHING
2940  // %res:_(sN) = G_OR %x, %y
2941  //
2942  // Eliminate the G_OR when it is known that x | y == x or x | y == y.
2943  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_OR);
2944  if (!KB)
2945  return false;
2946 
2947  Register OrDst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
2948  Register LHS = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
2949  Register RHS = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
2950  KnownBits LHSBits = KB->getKnownBits(LHS);
2951  KnownBits RHSBits = KB->getKnownBits(RHS);
2952 
2953  // Check that x | Mask == x.
2954  // x | 0 == x, always
2955  // x | 1 == x, only if x is also 1
2956  // Meaning Mask has no effect if every bit is either zero in Mask or one in x.
2957  //
2958  // Check if we can replace OrDst with the LHS of the G_OR
2959  if (canReplaceReg(OrDst, LHS, MRI) &&
2960  (LHSBits.One | RHSBits.Zero).isAllOnes()) {
2961  Replacement = LHS;
2962  return true;
2963  }
2964 
2965  // Check if we can replace OrDst with the RHS of the G_OR
2966  if (canReplaceReg(OrDst, RHS, MRI) &&
2967  (LHSBits.Zero | RHSBits.One).isAllOnes()) {
2968  Replacement = RHS;
2969  return true;
2970  }
2971 
2972  return false;
2973 }

2975 bool CombinerHelper::matchRedundantSExtInReg(MachineInstr &MI) {
2976  // If the input is already sign extended, just drop the extension.
2977  Register Src = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
2978  unsigned ExtBits = MI.getOperand(2).getImm();
2979  unsigned TypeSize = MRI.getType(Src).getScalarSizeInBits();
2980  return KB->computeNumSignBits(Src) >= (TypeSize - ExtBits + 1);
2981 }

2983 static bool isConstValidTrue(const TargetLowering &TLI, unsigned ScalarSizeBits,
2984  int64_t Cst, bool IsVector, bool IsFP) {
2985  // For i1, Cst will always be -1 regardless of boolean contents.
2986  return (ScalarSizeBits == 1 && Cst == -1) ||
2987  isConstTrueVal(TLI, Cst, IsVector, IsFP);
2988 }
2989 
2990 bool CombinerHelper::matchNotCmp(MachineInstr &MI,
2991  SmallVectorImpl<Register> &RegsToNegate) {
2992  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_XOR);
2993  LLT Ty = MRI.getType(MI.getOperand(0).getReg());
2994  const auto &TLI = *Builder.getMF().getSubtarget().getTargetLowering();
2995  Register XorSrc;
2996  Register CstReg;
2997  // We match xor(src, true) here.
2998  if (!mi_match(MI.getOperand(0).getReg(), MRI,
2999  m_GXor(m_Reg(XorSrc), m_Reg(CstReg))))
3000  return false;
3001 
3002  if (!MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(XorSrc))
3003  return false;
3004 
3005  // Check that XorSrc is the root of a tree of comparisons combined with ANDs
3006  // and ORs. The suffix of RegsToNegate starting from index I is used a work
3007  // list of tree nodes to visit.
3008  RegsToNegate.push_back(XorSrc);
3009  // Remember whether the comparisons are all integer or all floating point.
3010  bool IsInt = false;
3011  bool IsFP = false;
3012  for (unsigned I = 0; I < RegsToNegate.size(); ++I) {
3013  Register Reg = RegsToNegate[I];
3014  if (!MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(Reg))
3015  return false;
3016  MachineInstr *Def = MRI.getVRegDef(Reg);
3017  switch (Def->getOpcode()) {
3018  default:
3019  // Don't match if the tree contains anything other than ANDs, ORs and
3020  // comparisons.
3021  return false;
3022  case TargetOpcode::G_ICMP:
3023  if (IsFP)
3024  return false;
3025  IsInt = true;
3026  // When we apply the combine we will invert the predicate.
3027  break;
3028  case TargetOpcode::G_FCMP:
3029  if (IsInt)
3030  return false;
3031  IsFP = true;
3032  // When we apply the combine we will invert the predicate.
3033  break;
3034  case TargetOpcode::G_AND:
3035  case TargetOpcode::G_OR:
3036  // Implement De Morgan's laws:
3037  // ~(x & y) -> ~x | ~y
3038  // ~(x | y) -> ~x & ~y
3039  // When we apply the combine we will change the opcode and recursively
3040  // negate the operands.
3041  RegsToNegate.push_back(Def->getOperand(1).getReg());
3042  RegsToNegate.push_back(Def->getOperand(2).getReg());
3043  break;
3044  }
3045  }
3046 
3047  // Now we know whether the comparisons are integer or floating point, check
3048  // the constant in the xor.
3049  int64_t Cst;
3050  if (Ty.isVector()) {
3051  MachineInstr *CstDef = MRI.getVRegDef(CstReg);
3052  auto MaybeCst = getIConstantSplatSExtVal(*CstDef, MRI);
3053  if (!MaybeCst)
3054  return false;
3055  if (!isConstValidTrue(TLI, Ty.getScalarSizeInBits(), *MaybeCst, true, IsFP))
3056  return false;
3057  } else {
3058  if (!mi_match(CstReg, MRI, m_ICst(Cst)))
3059  return false;
3060  if (!isConstValidTrue(TLI, Ty.getSizeInBits(), Cst, false, IsFP))
3061  return false;
3062  }
3063 
3064  return true;
3065 }
3066 
3067 void CombinerHelper::applyNotCmp(MachineInstr &MI,
3068  SmallVectorImpl<Register> &RegsToNegate) {
3069  for (Register Reg : RegsToNegate) {
3070  MachineInstr *Def = MRI.getVRegDef(Reg);
3071  Observer.changingInstr(*Def);
3072  // For each comparison, invert the opcode. For each AND and OR, change the
3073  // opcode.
3074  switch (Def->getOpcode()) {
3075  default:
3076  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected opcode");
3077  case TargetOpcode::G_ICMP:
3078  case TargetOpcode::G_FCMP: {
3079  MachineOperand &PredOp = Def->getOperand(1);
3080  CmpInst::Predicate NewP = CmpInst::getInversePredicate(
3081  (CmpInst::Predicate)PredOp.getPredicate());
3082  PredOp.setPredicate(NewP);
3083  break;
3084  }
3085  case TargetOpcode::G_AND:
3086  Def->setDesc(Builder.getTII().get(TargetOpcode::G_OR));
3087  break;
3088  case TargetOpcode::G_OR:
3089  Def->setDesc(Builder.getTII().get(TargetOpcode::G_AND));
3090  break;
3091  }
3092  Observer.changedInstr(*Def);
3093  }
3094 
3095  replaceRegWith(MRI, MI.getOperand(0).getReg(), MI.getOperand(1).getReg());
3096  MI.eraseFromParent();
3097 }
3098 
3099 bool CombinerHelper::matchXorOfAndWithSameReg(
3100  MachineInstr &MI, std::pair<Register, Register> &MatchInfo) {
3101  // Match (xor (and x, y), y) (or any of its commuted cases)
3102  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_XOR);
3103  Register &X = MatchInfo.first;
3104  Register &Y = MatchInfo.second;
3105  Register AndReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
3106  Register SharedReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
3107 
3108  // Find a G_AND on either side of the G_XOR.
3109  // Look for one of
3110  //
3111  // (xor (and x, y), SharedReg)
3112  // (xor SharedReg, (and x, y))
3113  if (!mi_match(AndReg, MRI, m_GAnd(m_Reg(X), m_Reg(Y)))) {
3114  std::swap(AndReg, SharedReg);
3115  if (!mi_match(AndReg, MRI, m_GAnd(m_Reg(X), m_Reg(Y))))
3116  return false;
3117  }
3118 
3119  // Only do this if we'll eliminate the G_AND.
3120  if (!MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(AndReg))
3121  return false;
3122 
3123  // We can combine if SharedReg is the same as either the LHS or RHS of the
3124  // G_AND.
3125  if (Y != SharedReg)
3126  std::swap(X, Y);
3127  return Y == SharedReg;
3128 }
3129 
3130 void CombinerHelper::applyXorOfAndWithSameReg(
3131  MachineInstr &MI, std::pair<Register, Register> &MatchInfo) {
3132  // Fold (xor (and x, y), y) -> (and (not x), y)
3133  Builder.setInstrAndDebugLoc(MI);
3134  Register X, Y;
3135  std::tie(X, Y) = MatchInfo;
3136  auto Not = Builder.buildNot(MRI.getType(X), X);
3137  Observer.changingInstr(MI);
3138  MI.setDesc(Builder.getTII().get(TargetOpcode::G_AND));
3139  MI.getOperand(1).setReg(Not->getOperand(0).getReg());
3140  MI.getOperand(2).setReg(Y);
3141  Observer.changedInstr(MI);
3142 }

3170 /// The second source operand is known to be a power of 2.
3171 void CombinerHelper::applySimplifyURemByPow2(MachineInstr &MI) {
3172  Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
3173  Register Src0 = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
3174  Register Pow2Src1 = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
3175  LLT Ty = MRI.getType(DstReg);
3176  Builder.setInstrAndDebugLoc(MI);
3177 
3178  // Fold (urem x, pow2) -> (and x, pow2-1)
3179  auto NegOne = Builder.buildConstant(Ty, -1);
3180  auto Add = Builder.buildAdd(Ty, Pow2Src1, NegOne);
3181  Builder.buildAnd(DstReg, Src0, Add);

3185 bool CombinerHelper::matchFoldBinOpIntoSelect(MachineInstr &MI,
3186  unsigned &SelectOpNo) {
3187  Register LHS = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
3188  Register RHS = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
3189 
3190  Register OtherOperandReg = RHS;
3191  SelectOpNo = 1;
3192  MachineInstr *Select = MRI.getVRegDef(LHS);
3193 
3194  // Don't do this unless the old select is going away. We want to eliminate the
3195  // binary operator, not replace a binop with a select.
3196  if (Select->getOpcode() != TargetOpcode::G_SELECT ||
3197  !MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(LHS)) {
3198  OtherOperandReg = LHS;
3199  SelectOpNo = 2;
3200  Select = MRI.getVRegDef(RHS);
3201  if (Select->getOpcode() != TargetOpcode::G_SELECT ||
3202  !MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(RHS))
3203  return false;
3204  }
3205 
3206  MachineInstr *SelectLHS = MRI.getVRegDef(Select->getOperand(2).getReg());
3207  MachineInstr *SelectRHS = MRI.getVRegDef(Select->getOperand(3).getReg());
3208 
3209  if (!isConstantOrConstantVector(*SelectLHS, MRI,
3210  /*AllowFP*/ true,
3211  /*AllowOpaqueConstants*/ false))
3212  return false;
3213  if (!isConstantOrConstantVector(*SelectRHS, MRI,
3214  /*AllowFP*/ true,
3215  /*AllowOpaqueConstants*/ false))
3216  return false;
3217 
3218  unsigned BinOpcode = MI.getOpcode();
3219 
3220  // We know know one of the operands is a select of constants. Now verify that
3221  // the other binary operator operand is either a constant, or we can handle a
3222  // variable.
3223  bool CanFoldNonConst =
3224  (BinOpcode == TargetOpcode::G_AND || BinOpcode == TargetOpcode::G_OR) &&
3225  (isNullOrNullSplat(*SelectLHS, MRI) ||
3226  isAllOnesOrAllOnesSplat(*SelectLHS, MRI)) &&
3227  (isNullOrNullSplat(*SelectRHS, MRI) ||
3228  isAllOnesOrAllOnesSplat(*SelectRHS, MRI));
3229  if (CanFoldNonConst)
3230  return true;
3231 
3232  return isConstantOrConstantVector(*MRI.getVRegDef(OtherOperandReg), MRI,
3233  /*AllowFP*/ true,
3234  /*AllowOpaqueConstants*/ false);
3235 }
3236 
3237 /// \p SelectOperand is the operand in binary operator \p MI that is the select
3238 /// to fold.
3239 bool CombinerHelper::applyFoldBinOpIntoSelect(MachineInstr &MI,
3240  const unsigned &SelectOperand) {
3241  Builder.setInstrAndDebugLoc(MI);
3242 
3243  Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
3244  Register LHS = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
3245  Register RHS = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
3246  MachineInstr *Select = MRI.getVRegDef(MI.getOperand(SelectOperand).getReg());
3247 
3248  Register SelectCond = Select->getOperand(1).getReg();
3249  Register SelectTrue = Select->getOperand(2).getReg();
3250  Register SelectFalse = Select->getOperand(3).getReg();
3251 
3252  LLT Ty = MRI.getType(Dst);
3253  unsigned BinOpcode = MI.getOpcode();
3254 
3255  Register FoldTrue, FoldFalse;
3256 
3257  // We have a select-of-constants followed by a binary operator with a
3258  // constant. Eliminate the binop by pulling the constant math into the select.
3259  // Example: add (select Cond, CT, CF), CBO --> select Cond, CT + CBO, CF + CBO
3260  if (SelectOperand == 1) {
3261  // TODO: SelectionDAG verifies this actually constant folds before
3262  // committing to the combine.
3263 
3264  FoldTrue = Builder.buildInstr(BinOpcode, {Ty}, {SelectTrue, RHS}).getReg(0);
3265  FoldFalse =
3266  Builder.buildInstr(BinOpcode, {Ty}, {SelectFalse, RHS}).getReg(0);
3267  } else {
3268  FoldTrue = Builder.buildInstr(BinOpcode, {Ty}, {LHS, SelectTrue}).getReg(0);
3269  FoldFalse =
3270  Builder.buildInstr(BinOpcode, {Ty}, {LHS, SelectFalse}).getReg(0);
3271  }
3272 
3273  Builder.buildSelect(Dst, SelectCond, FoldTrue, FoldFalse, MI.getFlags());
3274  MI.eraseFromParent();
3275 
3276  return true;
3277 }
3278 
3279 std::optional<SmallVector<Register, 8>>
3280 CombinerHelper::findCandidatesForLoadOrCombine(const MachineInstr *Root) const {
3281  assert(Root->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_OR && "Expected G_OR only!");
3282  // We want to detect if Root is part of a tree which represents a bunch
3283  // of loads being merged into a larger load. We'll try to recognize patterns
3284  // like, for example:
3285  //
3286  // Reg Reg
3287  // \ /
3288  // OR_1 Reg
3289  // \ /
3290  // OR_2
3291  // \ Reg
3292  // .. /
3293  // Root
3294  //
3295  // Reg Reg Reg Reg
3296  // \ / \ /
3297  // OR_1 OR_2
3298  // \ /
3299  // \ /
3300  // ...
3301  // Root
3302  //
3303  // Each "Reg" may have been produced by a load + some arithmetic. This
3304  // function will save each of them.
3305  SmallVector<Register, 8> RegsToVisit;
3306  SmallVector<const MachineInstr *, 7> Ors = {Root};
3307 
3308  // In the "worst" case, we're dealing with a load for each byte. So, there
3309  // are at most #bytes - 1 ORs.
3310  const unsigned MaxIter =
3311  MRI.getType(Root->getOperand(0).getReg()).getSizeInBytes() - 1;
3312  for (unsigned Iter = 0; Iter < MaxIter; ++Iter) {
3313  if (Ors.empty())
3314  break;
3315  const MachineInstr *Curr = Ors.pop_back_val();
3316  Register OrLHS = Curr->getOperand(1).getReg();
3317  Register OrRHS = Curr->getOperand(2).getReg();
3318 
3319  // In the combine, we want to elimate the entire tree.
3320  if (!MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(OrLHS) || !MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(OrRHS))
3321  return std::nullopt;
3322 
3323  // If it's a G_OR, save it and continue to walk. If it's not, then it's
3324  // something that may be a load + arithmetic.
3325  if (const MachineInstr *Or = getOpcodeDef(TargetOpcode::G_OR, OrLHS, MRI))
3326  Ors.push_back(Or);
3327  else
3328  RegsToVisit.push_back(OrLHS);
3329  if (const MachineInstr *Or = getOpcodeDef(TargetOpcode::G_OR, OrRHS, MRI))
3330  Ors.push_back(Or);
3331  else
3332  RegsToVisit.push_back(OrRHS);
3333  }
3334 
3335  // We're going to try and merge each register into a wider power-of-2 type,
3336  // so we ought to have an even number of registers.
3337  if (RegsToVisit.empty() || RegsToVisit.size() % 2 != 0)
3338  return std::nullopt;
3339  return RegsToVisit;
3340 }
3341 
3342 /// Helper function for findLoadOffsetsForLoadOrCombine.
3343 ///
3344 /// Check if \p Reg is the result of loading a \p MemSizeInBits wide value,
3345 /// and then moving that value into a specific byte offset.
3346 ///
3347 /// e.g. x[i] << 24
3348 ///
3349 /// \returns The load instruction and the byte offset it is moved into.
3350 static std::optional<std::pair<GZExtLoad *, int64_t>>
3351 matchLoadAndBytePosition(Register Reg, unsigned MemSizeInBits,
3352  const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) {
3353  assert(MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(Reg) &&
3354  "Expected Reg to only have one non-debug use?");
3355  Register MaybeLoad;
3356  int64_t Shift;
3357  if (!mi_match(Reg, MRI,
3358  m_OneNonDBGUse(m_GShl(m_Reg(MaybeLoad), m_ICst(Shift))))) {
3359  Shift = 0;
3360  MaybeLoad = Reg;
3361  }
3362 
3363  if (Shift % MemSizeInBits != 0)
3364  return std::nullopt;
3365 
3366  // TODO: Handle other types of loads.
3367  auto *Load = getOpcodeDef<GZExtLoad>(MaybeLoad, MRI);
3368  if (!Load)
3369  return std::nullopt;
3370 
3371  if (!Load->isUnordered() || Load->getMemSizeInBits() != MemSizeInBits)
3372  return std::nullopt;
3373 
3374  return std::make_pair(Load, Shift / MemSizeInBits);
3375 }
3376 
3377 std::optional<std::tuple<GZExtLoad *, int64_t, GZExtLoad *>>
3378 CombinerHelper::findLoadOffsetsForLoadOrCombine(
3379  SmallDenseMap<int64_t, int64_t, 8> &MemOffset2Idx,
3380  const SmallVector<Register, 8> &RegsToVisit, const unsigned MemSizeInBits) {
3381 
3382  // Each load found for the pattern. There should be one for each RegsToVisit.
3383  SmallSetVector<const MachineInstr *, 8> Loads;
3384 
3385  // The lowest index used in any load. (The lowest "i" for each x[i].)
3386  int64_t LowestIdx = INT64_MAX;
3387 
3388  // The load which uses the lowest index.
3389  GZExtLoad *LowestIdxLoad = nullptr;
3390 
3391  // Keeps track of the load indices we see. We shouldn't see any indices twice.
3392  SmallSet<int64_t, 8> SeenIdx;
3393 
3394  // Ensure each load is in the same MBB.
3395  // TODO: Support multiple MachineBasicBlocks.
3396  MachineBasicBlock *MBB = nullptr;
3397  const MachineMemOperand *MMO = nullptr;
3398 
3399  // Earliest instruction-order load in the pattern.
3400  GZExtLoad *EarliestLoad = nullptr;
3401 
3402  // Latest instruction-order load in the pattern.
3403  GZExtLoad *LatestLoad = nullptr;
3404 
3405  // Base pointer which every load should share.
3406  Register BasePtr;
3407 
3408  // We want to find a load for each register. Each load should have some
3409  // appropriate bit twiddling arithmetic. During this loop, we will also keep
3410  // track of the load which uses the lowest index. Later, we will check if we
3411  // can use its pointer in the final, combined load.
3412  for (auto Reg : RegsToVisit) {
3413  // Find the load, and find the position that it will end up in (e.g. a
3414  // shifted) value.
3415  auto LoadAndPos = matchLoadAndBytePosition(Reg, MemSizeInBits, MRI);
3416  if (!LoadAndPos)
3417  return std::nullopt;
3418  GZExtLoad *Load;
3419  int64_t DstPos;
3420  std::tie(Load, DstPos) = *LoadAndPos;
3421 
3422  // TODO: Handle multiple MachineBasicBlocks. Currently not handled because
3423  // it is difficult to check for stores/calls/etc between loads.
3424  MachineBasicBlock *LoadMBB = Load->getParent();
3425  if (!MBB)
3426  MBB = LoadMBB;
3427  if (LoadMBB != MBB)
3428  return std::nullopt;
3429 
3430  // Make sure that the MachineMemOperands of every seen load are compatible.
3431  auto &LoadMMO = Load->getMMO();
3432  if (!MMO)
3433  MMO = &LoadMMO;
3434  if (MMO->getAddrSpace() != LoadMMO.getAddrSpace())
3435  return std::nullopt;
3436 
3437  // Find out what the base pointer and index for the load is.
3438  Register LoadPtr;
3439  int64_t Idx;
3440  if (!mi_match(Load->getOperand(1).getReg(), MRI,
3441  m_GPtrAdd(m_Reg(LoadPtr), m_ICst(Idx)))) {
3442  LoadPtr = Load->getOperand(1).getReg();
3443  Idx = 0;
3444  }
3445 
3446  // Don't combine things like a[i], a[i] -> a bigger load.
3447  if (!SeenIdx.insert(Idx).second)
3448  return std::nullopt;
3449 
3450  // Every load must share the same base pointer; don't combine things like:
3451  //
3452  // a[i], b[i + 1] -> a bigger load.
3453  if (!BasePtr.isValid())
3454  BasePtr = LoadPtr;
3455  if (BasePtr != LoadPtr)
3456  return std::nullopt;
3457 
3458  if (Idx < LowestIdx) {
3459  LowestIdx = Idx;
3460  LowestIdxLoad = Load;
3461  }
3462 
3463  // Keep track of the byte offset that this load ends up at. If we have seen
3464  // the byte offset, then stop here. We do not want to combine:
3465  //
3466  // a[i] << 16, a[i + k] << 16 -> a bigger load.
3467  if (!MemOffset2Idx.try_emplace(DstPos, Idx).second)
3468  return std::nullopt;
3469  Loads.insert(Load);
3470 
3471  // Keep track of the position of the earliest/latest loads in the pattern.
3472  // We will check that there are no load fold barriers between them later
3473  // on.
3474  //
3475  // FIXME: Is there a better way to check for load fold barriers?
3476  if (!EarliestLoad || dominates(*Load, *EarliestLoad))
3477  EarliestLoad = Load;
3478  if (!LatestLoad || dominates(*LatestLoad, *Load))
3479  LatestLoad = Load;
3480  }
3481 
3482  // We found a load for each register. Let's check if each load satisfies the
3483  // pattern.
3484  assert(Loads.size() == RegsToVisit.size() &&
3485  "Expected to find a load for each register?");
3486  assert(EarliestLoad != LatestLoad && EarliestLoad &&
3487  LatestLoad && "Expected at least two loads?");
3488 
3489  // Check if there are any stores, calls, etc. between any of the loads. If
3490  // there are, then we can't safely perform the combine.
3491  //
3492  // MaxIter is chosen based off the (worst case) number of iterations it
3493  // typically takes to succeed in the LLVM test suite plus some padding.
3494  //
3495  // FIXME: Is there a better way to check for load fold barriers?
3496  const unsigned MaxIter = 20;
3497  unsigned Iter = 0;
3498  for (const auto &MI : instructionsWithoutDebug(EarliestLoad->getIterator(),
3499  LatestLoad->getIterator())) {
3500  if (Loads.count(&MI))
3501  continue;
3502  if (MI.isLoadFoldBarrier())
3503  return std::nullopt;
3504  if (Iter++ == MaxIter)
3505  return std::nullopt;
3506  }
3507 
3508  return std::make_tuple(LowestIdxLoad, LowestIdx, LatestLoad);
3509 }
3510 
3511 bool CombinerHelper::matchLoadOrCombine(
3512  MachineInstr &MI, std::function<void(MachineIRBuilder &)> &MatchInfo) {
3513  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_OR);
3514  MachineFunction &MF = *MI.getMF();
3515  // Assuming a little-endian target, transform:
3516  // s8 *a = ...
3517  // s32 val = a[0] | (a[1] << 8) | (a[2] << 16) | (a[3] << 24)
3518  // =>
3519  // s32 val = *((i32)a)
3520  //
3521  // s8 *a = ...
3522  // s32 val = (a[0] << 24) | (a[1] << 16) | (a[2] << 8) | a[3]
3523  // =>
3524  // s32 val = BSWAP(*((s32)a))
3525  Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
3526  LLT Ty = MRI.getType(Dst);
3527  if (Ty.isVector())
3528  return false;
3529 
3530  // We need to combine at least two loads into this type. Since the smallest
3531  // possible load is into a byte, we need at least a 16-bit wide type.
3532  const unsigned WideMemSizeInBits = Ty.getSizeInBits();
3533  if (WideMemSizeInBits < 16 || WideMemSizeInBits % 8 != 0)
3534  return false;
3535 
3536  // Match a collection of non-OR instructions in the pattern.
3537  auto RegsToVisit = findCandidatesForLoadOrCombine(&MI);
3538  if (!RegsToVisit)
3539  return false;
3540 
3541  // We have a collection of non-OR instructions. Figure out how wide each of
3542  // the small loads should be based off of the number of potential loads we
3543  // found.
3544  const unsigned NarrowMemSizeInBits = WideMemSizeInBits / RegsToVisit->size();
3545  if (NarrowMemSizeInBits % 8 != 0)
3546  return false;
3547 
3548  // Check if each register feeding into each OR is a load from the same
3549  // base pointer + some arithmetic.
3550  //
3551  // e.g. a[0], a[1] << 8, a[2] << 16, etc.
3552  //
3553  // Also verify that each of these ends up putting a[i] into the same memory
3554  // offset as a load into a wide type would.
3555  SmallDenseMap<int64_t, int64_t, 8> MemOffset2Idx;
3556  GZExtLoad *LowestIdxLoad, *LatestLoad;
3557  int64_t LowestIdx;
3558  auto MaybeLoadInfo = findLoadOffsetsForLoadOrCombine(
3559  MemOffset2Idx, *RegsToVisit, NarrowMemSizeInBits);
3560  if (!MaybeLoadInfo)
3561  return false;
3562  std::tie(LowestIdxLoad, LowestIdx, LatestLoad) = *MaybeLoadInfo;
3563 
3564  // We have a bunch of loads being OR'd together. Using the addresses + offsets
3565  // we found before, check if this corresponds to a big or little endian byte
3566  // pattern. If it does, then we can represent it using a load + possibly a
3567  // BSWAP.
3568  bool IsBigEndianTarget = MF.getDataLayout().isBigEndian();
3569  std::optional<bool> IsBigEndian = isBigEndian(MemOffset2Idx, LowestIdx);
3570  if (!IsBigEndian)
3571  return false;
3572  bool NeedsBSwap = IsBigEndianTarget != *IsBigEndian;
3573  if (NeedsBSwap && !isLegalOrBeforeLegalizer({TargetOpcode::G_BSWAP, {Ty}}))
3574  return false;
3575 
3576  // Make sure that the load from the lowest index produces offset 0 in the
3577  // final value.
3578  //
3579  // This ensures that we won't combine something like this:
3580  //
3581  // load x[i] -> byte 2
3582  // load x[i+1] -> byte 0 ---> wide_load x[i]
3583  // load x[i+2] -> byte 1
3584  const unsigned NumLoadsInTy = WideMemSizeInBits / NarrowMemSizeInBits;
3585  const unsigned ZeroByteOffset =
3586  *IsBigEndian
3587  ? bigEndianByteAt(NumLoadsInTy, 0)
3588  : littleEndianByteAt(NumLoadsInTy, 0);
3589  auto ZeroOffsetIdx = MemOffset2Idx.find(ZeroByteOffset);
3590  if (ZeroOffsetIdx == MemOffset2Idx.end() ||
3591  ZeroOffsetIdx->second != LowestIdx)
3592  return false;
3593 
3594  // We wil reuse the pointer from the load which ends up at byte offset 0. It
3595  // may not use index 0.
3596  Register Ptr = LowestIdxLoad->getPointerReg();
3597  const MachineMemOperand &MMO = LowestIdxLoad->getMMO();
3598  LegalityQuery::MemDesc MMDesc(MMO);
3599  MMDesc.MemoryTy = Ty;
3600  if (!isLegalOrBeforeLegalizer(
3601  {TargetOpcode::G_LOAD, {Ty, MRI.getType(Ptr)}, {MMDesc}}))
3602  return false;
3603  auto PtrInfo = MMO.getPointerInfo();
3604  auto *NewMMO = MF.getMachineMemOperand(&MMO, PtrInfo, WideMemSizeInBits / 8);
3605 
3606  // Load must be allowed and fast on the target.
3607  LLVMContext &C = MF.getFunction().getContext();
3608  auto &DL = MF.getDataLayout();
3609  unsigned Fast = 0;
3610  if (!getTargetLowering().allowsMemoryAccess(C, DL, Ty, *NewMMO, &Fast) ||
3611  !Fast)
3612  return false;
3613 
3614  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &MIB) {
3615  MIB.setInstrAndDebugLoc(*LatestLoad);
3616  Register LoadDst = NeedsBSwap ? MRI.cloneVirtualRegister(Dst) : Dst;
3617  MIB.buildLoad(LoadDst, Ptr, *NewMMO);
3618  if (NeedsBSwap)
3619  MIB.buildBSwap(Dst, LoadDst);
3620  };
3621  return true;
3622 }
3623 
3624 /// Check if the store \p Store is a truncstore that can be merged. That is,
3625 /// it's a store of a shifted value of \p SrcVal. If \p SrcVal is an empty
3626 /// Register then it does not need to match and SrcVal is set to the source
3627 /// value found.
3628 /// On match, returns the start byte offset of the \p SrcVal that is being
3629 /// stored.
3630 static std::optional<int64_t>
3631 getTruncStoreByteOffset(GStore &Store, Register &SrcVal,
3632  MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) {
3633  Register TruncVal;
3634  if (!mi_match(Store.getValueReg(), MRI, m_GTrunc(m_Reg(TruncVal))))
3635  return std::nullopt;
3636 
3637  // The shift amount must be a constant multiple of the narrow type.
3638  // It is translated to the offset address in the wide source value "y".
3639  //
3640  // x = G_LSHR y, ShiftAmtC
3641  // s8 z = G_TRUNC x
3642  // store z, ...
3643  Register FoundSrcVal;
3644  int64_t ShiftAmt;
3645  if (!mi_match(TruncVal, MRI,
3646  m_any_of(m_GLShr(m_Reg(FoundSrcVal), m_ICst(ShiftAmt)),
3647  m_GAShr(m_Reg(FoundSrcVal), m_ICst(ShiftAmt))))) {
3648  if (!SrcVal.isValid() || TruncVal == SrcVal) {
3649  if (!SrcVal.isValid())
3650  SrcVal = TruncVal;
3651  return 0; // If it's the lowest index store.
3652  }
3653  return std::nullopt;
3654  }
3655 
3656  unsigned NarrowBits = Store.getMMO().getMemoryType().getScalarSizeInBits();
3657  if (ShiftAmt % NarrowBits!= 0)
3658  return std::nullopt;
3659  const unsigned Offset = ShiftAmt / NarrowBits;
3660 
3661  if (SrcVal.isValid() && FoundSrcVal != SrcVal)
3662  return std::nullopt;
3663 
3664  if (!SrcVal.isValid())
3665  SrcVal = FoundSrcVal;
3666  else if (MRI.getType(SrcVal) != MRI.getType(FoundSrcVal))
3667  return std::nullopt;
3668  return Offset;
3669 }
3670 
3671 /// Match a pattern where a wide type scalar value is stored by several narrow
3672 /// stores. Fold it into a single store or a BSWAP and a store if the targets
3673 /// supports it.
3674 ///
3675 /// Assuming little endian target:
3676 /// i8 *p = ...
3677 /// i32 val = ...
3678 /// p[0] = (val >> 0) & 0xFF;
3679 /// p[1] = (val >> 8) & 0xFF;
3680 /// p[2] = (val >> 16) & 0xFF;
3681 /// p[3] = (val >> 24) & 0xFF;
3682 /// =>
3683 /// *((i32)p) = val;
3684 ///
3685 /// i8 *p = ...
3686 /// i32 val = ...
3687 /// p[0] = (val >> 24) & 0xFF;
3688 /// p[1] = (val >> 16) & 0xFF;
3689 /// p[2] = (val >> 8) & 0xFF;
3690 /// p[3] = (val >> 0) & 0xFF;
3691 /// =>
3692 /// *((i32)p) = BSWAP(val);
3693 bool CombinerHelper::matchTruncStoreMerge(MachineInstr &MI,
3694  MergeTruncStoresInfo &MatchInfo) {
3695  auto &StoreMI = cast<GStore>(MI);
3696  LLT MemTy = StoreMI.getMMO().getMemoryType();
3697 
3698  // We only handle merging simple stores of 1-4 bytes.
3699  if (!MemTy.isScalar())
3700  return false;
3701  switch (MemTy.getSizeInBits()) {
3702  case 8:
3703  case 16:
3704  case 32:
3705  break;
3706  default:
3707  return false;
3708  }
3709  if (!StoreMI.isSimple())
3710  return false;
3711 
3712  // We do a simple search for mergeable stores prior to this one.
3713  // Any potential alias hazard along the way terminates the search.
3714  SmallVector<GStore *> FoundStores;
3715 
3716  // We're looking for:
3717  // 1) a (store(trunc(...)))
3718  // 2) of an LSHR/ASHR of a single wide value, by the appropriate shift to get
3719  // the partial value stored.
3720  // 3) where the offsets form either a little or big-endian sequence.
3721 
3722  auto &LastStore = StoreMI;
3723 
3724  // The single base pointer that all stores must use.
3725  Register BaseReg;
3726  int64_t LastOffset;
3727  if (!mi_match(LastStore.getPointerReg(), MRI,
3728  m_GPtrAdd(m_Reg(BaseReg), m_ICst(LastOffset)))) {
3729  BaseReg = LastStore.getPointerReg();
3730  LastOffset = 0;
3731  }
3732 
3733  GStore *LowestIdxStore = &LastStore;
3734  int64_t LowestIdxOffset = LastOffset;
3735 
3736  Register WideSrcVal;
3737  auto LowestShiftAmt = getTruncStoreByteOffset(LastStore, WideSrcVal, MRI);
3738  if (!LowestShiftAmt)
3739  return false; // Didn't match a trunc.
3740  assert(WideSrcVal.isValid());
3741 
3742  LLT WideStoreTy = MRI.getType(WideSrcVal);
3743  // The wide type might not be a multiple of the memory type, e.g. s48 and s32.
3744  if (WideStoreTy.getSizeInBits() % MemTy.getSizeInBits() != 0)
3745  return false;
3746  const unsigned NumStoresRequired =
3747  WideStoreTy.getSizeInBits() / MemTy.getSizeInBits();
3748 
3749  SmallVector<int64_t, 8> OffsetMap(NumStoresRequired, INT64_MAX);
3750  OffsetMap[*LowestShiftAmt] = LastOffset;
3751  FoundStores.emplace_back(&LastStore);
3752 
3753  // Search the block up for more stores.
3754  // We use a search threshold of 10 instructions here because the combiner
3755  // works top-down within a block, and we don't want to search an unbounded
3756  // number of predecessor instructions trying to find matching stores.
3757  // If we moved this optimization into a separate pass then we could probably
3758  // use a more efficient search without having a hard-coded threshold.
3759  const int MaxInstsToCheck = 10;
3760  int NumInstsChecked = 0;
3761  for (auto II = ++LastStore.getReverseIterator();
3762  II != LastStore.getParent()->rend() && NumInstsChecked < MaxInstsToCheck;
3763  ++II) {
3764  NumInstsChecked++;
3765  GStore *NewStore;
3766  if ((NewStore = dyn_cast<GStore>(&*II))) {
3767  if (NewStore->getMMO().getMemoryType() != MemTy || !NewStore->isSimple())
3768  break;
3769  } else if (II->isLoadFoldBarrier() || II->mayLoad()) {
3770  break;
3771  } else {
3772  continue; // This is a safe instruction we can look past.
3773  }
3774 
3775  Register NewBaseReg;
3776  int64_t MemOffset;
3777  // Check we're storing to the same base + some offset.
3778  if (!mi_match(NewStore->getPointerReg(), MRI,
3779  m_GPtrAdd(m_Reg(NewBaseReg), m_ICst(MemOffset)))) {
3780  NewBaseReg = NewStore->getPointerReg();
3781  MemOffset = 0;
3782  }
3783  if (BaseReg != NewBaseReg)
3784  break;
3785 
3786  auto ShiftByteOffset = getTruncStoreByteOffset(*NewStore, WideSrcVal, MRI);
3787  if (!ShiftByteOffset)
3788  break;
3789  if (MemOffset < LowestIdxOffset) {
3790  LowestIdxOffset = MemOffset;
3791  LowestIdxStore = NewStore;
3792  }
3793 
3794  // Map the offset in the store and the offset in the combined value, and
3795  // early return if it has been set before.
3796  if (*ShiftByteOffset < 0 || *ShiftByteOffset >= NumStoresRequired ||
3797  OffsetMap[*ShiftByteOffset] != INT64_MAX)
3798  break;
3799  OffsetMap[*ShiftByteOffset] = MemOffset;
3800 
3801  FoundStores.emplace_back(NewStore);
3802  // Reset counter since we've found a matching inst.
3803  NumInstsChecked = 0;
3804  if (FoundStores.size() == NumStoresRequired)
3805  break;
3806  }
3807 
3808  if (FoundStores.size() != NumStoresRequired) {
3809  return false;
3810  }
3811 
3812  const auto &DL = LastStore.getMF()->getDataLayout();
3813  auto &C = LastStore.getMF()->getFunction().getContext();
3814  // Check that a store of the wide type is both allowed and fast on the target
3815  unsigned Fast = 0;
3816  bool Allowed = getTargetLowering().allowsMemoryAccess(
3817  C, DL, WideStoreTy, LowestIdxStore->getMMO(), &Fast);
3818  if (!Allowed || !Fast)
3819  return false;
3820 
3821  // Check if the pieces of the value are going to the expected places in memory
3822  // to merge the stores.
3823  unsigned NarrowBits = MemTy.getScalarSizeInBits();
3824  auto checkOffsets = [&](bool MatchLittleEndian) {
3825  if (MatchLittleEndian) {
3826  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumStoresRequired; ++i)
3827  if (OffsetMap[i] != i * (NarrowBits / 8) + LowestIdxOffset)
3828  return false;
3829  } else { // MatchBigEndian by reversing loop counter.
3830  for (unsigned i = 0, j = NumStoresRequired - 1; i != NumStoresRequired;
3831  ++i, --j)
3832  if (OffsetMap[j] != i * (NarrowBits / 8) + LowestIdxOffset)
3833  return false;
3834  }
3835  return true;
3836  };
3837 
3838  // Check if the offsets line up for the native data layout of this target.
3839  bool NeedBswap = false;
3840  bool NeedRotate = false;
3841  if (!checkOffsets(DL.isLittleEndian())) {
3842  // Special-case: check if byte offsets line up for the opposite endian.
3843  if (NarrowBits == 8 && checkOffsets(DL.isBigEndian()))
3844  NeedBswap = true;
3845  else if (NumStoresRequired == 2 && checkOffsets(DL.isBigEndian()))
3846  NeedRotate = true;
3847  else
3848  return false;
3849  }
3850 
3851  if (NeedBswap &&
3852  !isLegalOrBeforeLegalizer({TargetOpcode::G_BSWAP, {WideStoreTy}}))
3853  return false;
3854  if (NeedRotate &&
3855  !isLegalOrBeforeLegalizer({TargetOpcode::G_ROTR, {WideStoreTy}}))
3856  return false;
3857 
3858  MatchInfo.NeedBSwap = NeedBswap;
3859  MatchInfo.NeedRotate = NeedRotate;
3860  MatchInfo.LowestIdxStore = LowestIdxStore;
3861  MatchInfo.WideSrcVal = WideSrcVal;
3862  MatchInfo.FoundStores = std::move(FoundStores);
3863  return true;
3864 }
3865 
3866 void CombinerHelper::applyTruncStoreMerge(MachineInstr &MI,
3867  MergeTruncStoresInfo &MatchInfo) {
3868 
3869  Builder.setInstrAndDebugLoc(MI);
3870  Register WideSrcVal = MatchInfo.WideSrcVal;
3871  LLT WideStoreTy = MRI.getType(WideSrcVal);
3872 
3873  if (MatchInfo.NeedBSwap) {
3874  WideSrcVal = Builder.buildBSwap(WideStoreTy, WideSrcVal).getReg(0);
3875  } else if (MatchInfo.NeedRotate) {
3876  assert(WideStoreTy.getSizeInBits() % 2 == 0 &&
3877  "Unexpected type for rotate");
3878  auto RotAmt =
3879  Builder.buildConstant(WideStoreTy, WideStoreTy.getSizeInBits() / 2);
3880  WideSrcVal =
3881  Builder.buildRotateRight(WideStoreTy, WideSrcVal, RotAmt).getReg(0);
3882  }
3883 
3884  Builder.buildStore(WideSrcVal, MatchInfo.LowestIdxStore->getPointerReg(),
3885  MatchInfo.LowestIdxStore->getMMO().getPointerInfo(),
3886  MatchInfo.LowestIdxStore->getMMO().getAlign());
3887 
3888  // Erase the old stores.
3889  for (auto *ST : MatchInfo.FoundStores)
3890  ST->eraseFromParent();
3891 }
3892 
3893 bool CombinerHelper::matchExtendThroughPhis(MachineInstr &MI,
3894  MachineInstr *&ExtMI) {
3895  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_PHI);
3896 
3897  Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
3898 
3899  // TODO: Extending a vector may be expensive, don't do this until heuristics
3900  // are better.
3901  if (MRI.getType(DstReg).isVector())
3902  return false;
3903 
3904  // Try to match a phi, whose only use is an extend.
3905  if (!MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(DstReg))
3906  return false;
3907  ExtMI = &*MRI.use_instr_nodbg_begin(DstReg);
3908  switch (ExtMI->getOpcode()) {
3909  case TargetOpcode::G_ANYEXT:
3910  return true; // G_ANYEXT is usually free.
3911  case TargetOpcode::G_ZEXT:
3912  case TargetOpcode::G_SEXT:
3913  break;
3914  default:
3915  return false;
3916  }
3917 
3918  // If the target is likely to fold this extend away, don't propagate.
3919  if (Builder.getTII().isExtendLikelyToBeFolded(*ExtMI, MRI))
3920  return false;
3921 
3922  // We don't want to propagate the extends unless there's a good chance that
3923  // they'll be optimized in some way.
3924  // Collect the unique incoming values.
3925  SmallPtrSet<MachineInstr *, 4> InSrcs;
3926  for (unsigned Idx = 1; Idx < MI.getNumOperands(); Idx += 2) {
3927  auto *DefMI = getDefIgnoringCopies(MI.getOperand(Idx).getReg(), MRI);
3928  switch (DefMI->getOpcode()) {
3929  case TargetOpcode::G_LOAD:
3930  case TargetOpcode::G_TRUNC:
3931  case TargetOpcode::G_SEXT:
3932  case TargetOpcode::G_ZEXT:
3933  case TargetOpcode::G_ANYEXT:
3934  case TargetOpcode::G_CONSTANT:
3935  InSrcs.insert(getDefIgnoringCopies(MI.getOperand(Idx).getReg(), MRI));
3936  // Don't try to propagate if there are too many places to create new
3937  // extends, chances are it'll increase code size.
3938  if (InSrcs.size() > 2)
3939  return false;
3940  break;
3941  default:
3942  return false;
3943  }
3944  }
3945  return true;
3946 }
3947 
3948 void CombinerHelper::applyExtendThroughPhis(MachineInstr &MI,
3949  MachineInstr *&ExtMI) {
3950  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_PHI);
3951  Register DstReg = ExtMI->getOperand(0).getReg();
3952  LLT ExtTy = MRI.getType(DstReg);
3953 
3954  // Propagate the extension into the block of each incoming reg's block.
3955  // Use a SetVector here because PHIs can have duplicate edges, and we want
3956  // deterministic iteration order.
3957  SmallSetVector<MachineInstr *, 8> SrcMIs;
3958  SmallDenseMap<MachineInstr *, MachineInstr *, 8> OldToNewSrcMap;
3959  for (unsigned SrcIdx = 1; SrcIdx < MI.getNumOperands(); SrcIdx += 2) {
3960  auto *SrcMI = MRI.getVRegDef(MI.getOperand(SrcIdx).getReg());
3961  if (!SrcMIs.insert(SrcMI))
3962  continue;
3963 
3964  // Build an extend after each src inst.
3965  auto *MBB = SrcMI->getParent();
3966  MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertPt = ++SrcMI->getIterator();
3967  if (InsertPt != MBB->end() && InsertPt->isPHI())
3968  InsertPt = MBB->getFirstNonPHI();
3969 
3970  Builder.setInsertPt(*SrcMI->getParent(), InsertPt);
3971  Builder.setDebugLoc(MI.getDebugLoc());
3972  auto NewExt = Builder.buildExtOrTrunc(ExtMI->getOpcode(), ExtTy,
3973  SrcMI->getOperand(0).getReg());
3974  OldToNewSrcMap[SrcMI] = NewExt;
3975  }
3976 
3977  // Create a new phi with the extended inputs.
3978  Builder.setInstrAndDebugLoc(MI);
3979  auto NewPhi = Builder.buildInstrNoInsert(TargetOpcode::G_PHI);
3980  NewPhi.addDef(DstReg);
3981  for (const MachineOperand &MO : llvm::drop_begin(MI.operands())) {
3982  if (!MO.isReg()) {
3983  NewPhi.addMBB(MO.getMBB());
3984  continue;
3985  }
3986  auto *NewSrc = OldToNewSrcMap[MRI.getVRegDef(MO.getReg())];
3987  NewPhi.addUse(NewSrc->getOperand(0).getReg());
3988  }
3989  Builder.insertInstr(NewPhi);
3990  ExtMI->eraseFromParent();
3991 }
3992 
3993 bool CombinerHelper::matchExtractVecEltBuildVec(MachineInstr &MI,
3994  Register &Reg) {
3995  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT);
3996  // If we have a constant index, look for a G_BUILD_VECTOR source
3997  // and find the source register that the index maps to.
3998  Register SrcVec = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
3999  LLT SrcTy = MRI.getType(SrcVec);
4000 
4001  auto Cst = getIConstantVRegValWithLookThrough(MI.getOperand(2).getReg(), MRI);
4002  if (!Cst || Cst->Value.getZExtValue() >= SrcTy.getNumElements())
4003  return false;
4004 
4005  unsigned VecIdx = Cst->Value.getZExtValue();
4006 
4007  // Check if we have a build_vector or build_vector_trunc with an optional
4008  // trunc in front.
4009  MachineInstr *SrcVecMI = MRI.getVRegDef(SrcVec);
4010  if (SrcVecMI->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_TRUNC) {
4011  SrcVecMI = MRI.getVRegDef(SrcVecMI->getOperand(1).getReg());
4012  }
4013 
4014  if (SrcVecMI->getOpcode() != TargetOpcode::G_BUILD_VECTOR &&
4015  SrcVecMI->getOpcode() != TargetOpcode::G_BUILD_VECTOR_TRUNC)
4016  return false;
4017 
4018  EVT Ty(getMVTForLLT(SrcTy));
4019  if (!MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(SrcVec) &&
4020  !getTargetLowering().aggressivelyPreferBuildVectorSources(Ty))
4021  return false;
4022 
4023  Reg = SrcVecMI->getOperand(VecIdx + 1).getReg();
4024  return true;
4025 }

4027 void CombinerHelper::applyExtractVecEltBuildVec(MachineInstr &MI,
4028  Register &Reg) {
4029  // Check the type of the register, since it may have come from a
4030  // G_BUILD_VECTOR_TRUNC.
4031  LLT ScalarTy = MRI.getType(Reg);
4032  Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
4033  LLT DstTy = MRI.getType(DstReg);
4034 
4035  Builder.setInstrAndDebugLoc(MI);
4036  if (ScalarTy != DstTy) {
4037  assert(ScalarTy.getSizeInBits() > DstTy.getSizeInBits());
4038  Builder.buildTrunc(DstReg, Reg);
4039  MI.eraseFromParent();
4040  return;
4041  }
4042  replaceSingleDefInstWithReg(MI, Reg);

4044 
4045 bool CombinerHelper::matchExtractAllEltsFromBuildVector(
4046  MachineInstr &MI,
4047  SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<Register, MachineInstr *>> &SrcDstPairs) {
4048  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_BUILD_VECTOR);
4049  // This combine tries to find build_vector's which have every source element
4050  // extracted using G_EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT. This can happen when transforms like
4051  // the masked load scalarization is run late in the pipeline. There's already
4052  // a combine for a similar pattern starting from the extract, but that
4053  // doesn't attempt to do it if there are multiple uses of the build_vector,
4054  // which in this case is true. Starting the combine from the build_vector
4055  // feels more natural than trying to find sibling nodes of extracts.
4056  // E.g.
4057  // %vec(<4 x s32>) = G_BUILD_VECTOR %s1(s32), %s2, %s3, %s4
4058  // %ext1 = G_EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT %vec, 0
4059  // %ext2 = G_EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT %vec, 1
4060  // %ext3 = G_EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT %vec, 2
4061  // %ext4 = G_EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT %vec, 3
4062  // ==>
4063  // replace ext{1,2,3,4} with %s{1,2,3,4}
4064 
4065  Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
4066  LLT DstTy = MRI.getType(DstReg);
4067  unsigned NumElts = DstTy.getNumElements();
4068 
4069  SmallBitVector ExtractedElts(NumElts);
4070  for (MachineInstr &II : MRI.use_nodbg_instructions(DstReg)) {
4071  if (II.getOpcode() != TargetOpcode::G_EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT)
4072  return false;
4073  auto Cst = getIConstantVRegVal(II.getOperand(2).getReg(), MRI);
4074  if (!Cst)
4075  return false;
4076  unsigned Idx = Cst->getZExtValue();
4077  if (Idx >= NumElts)
4078  return false; // Out of range.
4079  ExtractedElts.set(Idx);
4080  SrcDstPairs.emplace_back(
4081  std::make_pair(MI.getOperand(Idx + 1).getReg(), &II));
4082  }
4083  // Match if every element was extracted.
4084  return ExtractedElts.all();
4085 }
4086 
4087 void CombinerHelper::applyExtractAllEltsFromBuildVector(
4088  MachineInstr &MI,
4089  SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<Register, MachineInstr *>> &SrcDstPairs) {
4090  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_BUILD_VECTOR);
4091  for (auto &Pair : SrcDstPairs) {
4092  auto *ExtMI = Pair.second;
4093  replaceRegWith(MRI, ExtMI->getOperand(0).getReg(), Pair.first);
4094  ExtMI->eraseFromParent();
4095  }
4096  MI.eraseFromParent();
4097 }

4112 bool CombinerHelper::matchOrShiftToFunnelShift(MachineInstr &MI,
4113  BuildFnTy &MatchInfo) {
4114  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_OR);
4115 
4116  Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
4117  LLT Ty = MRI.getType(Dst);
4118  unsigned BitWidth = Ty.getScalarSizeInBits();
4119 
4120  Register ShlSrc, ShlAmt, LShrSrc, LShrAmt, Amt;
4121  unsigned FshOpc = 0;
4122 
4123  // Match (or (shl ...), (lshr ...)).
4124  if (!mi_match(Dst, MRI,
4125  // m_GOr() handles the commuted version as well.
4126  m_GOr(m_GShl(m_Reg(ShlSrc), m_Reg(ShlAmt)),
4127  m_GLShr(m_Reg(LShrSrc), m_Reg(LShrAmt)))))
4128  return false;
4129 
4130  // Given constants C0 and C1 such that C0 + C1 is bit-width:
4131  // (or (shl x, C0), (lshr y, C1)) -> (fshl x, y, C0) or (fshr x, y, C1)
4132  int64_t CstShlAmt, CstLShrAmt;
4133  if (mi_match(ShlAmt, MRI, m_ICstOrSplat(CstShlAmt)) &&
4134  mi_match(LShrAmt, MRI, m_ICstOrSplat(CstLShrAmt)) &&
4135  CstShlAmt + CstLShrAmt == BitWidth) {
4136  FshOpc = TargetOpcode::G_FSHR;
4137  Amt = LShrAmt;
4138 
4139  } else if (mi_match(LShrAmt, MRI,
4140  m_GSub(m_SpecificICstOrSplat(BitWidth), m_Reg(Amt))) &&
4141  ShlAmt == Amt) {
4142  // (or (shl x, amt), (lshr y, (sub bw, amt))) -> (fshl x, y, amt)
4143  FshOpc = TargetOpcode::G_FSHL;
4144 
4145  } else if (mi_match(ShlAmt, MRI,
4146  m_GSub(m_SpecificICstOrSplat(BitWidth), m_Reg(Amt))) &&
4147  LShrAmt == Amt) {
4148  // (or (shl x, (sub bw, amt)), (lshr y, amt)) -> (fshr x, y, amt)
4149  FshOpc = TargetOpcode::G_FSHR;
4150 
4151  } else {
4152  return false;
4153  }
4154 
4155  LLT AmtTy = MRI.getType(Amt);
4156  if (!isLegalOrBeforeLegalizer({FshOpc, {Ty, AmtTy}}))
4157  return false;
4158 
4159  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
4160  B.buildInstr(FshOpc, {Dst}, {ShlSrc, LShrSrc, Amt});
4161  };
4162  return true;
4163 }
4164 
4165 /// Match an FSHL or FSHR that can be combined to a ROTR or ROTL rotate.
4166 bool CombinerHelper::matchFunnelShiftToRotate(MachineInstr &MI) {
4167  unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode();
4168  assert(Opc == TargetOpcode::G_FSHL || Opc == TargetOpcode::G_FSHR);
4169  Register X = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
4170  Register Y = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
4171  if (X != Y)
4172  return false;
4173  unsigned RotateOpc =
4174  Opc == TargetOpcode::G_FSHL ? TargetOpcode::G_ROTL : TargetOpcode::G_ROTR;
4175  return isLegalOrBeforeLegalizer({RotateOpc, {MRI.getType(X), MRI.getType(Y)}});
4176 }

4178 void CombinerHelper::applyFunnelShiftToRotate(MachineInstr &MI) {
4179  unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode();
4180  assert(Opc == TargetOpcode::G_FSHL || Opc == TargetOpcode::G_FSHR);
4181  bool IsFSHL = Opc == TargetOpcode::G_FSHL;
4182  Observer.changingInstr(MI);
4183  MI.setDesc(Builder.getTII().get(IsFSHL ? TargetOpcode::G_ROTL
4184  : TargetOpcode::G_ROTR));
4185  MI.removeOperand(2);
4186  Observer.changedInstr(MI);
4187 }

4189 // Fold (rot x, c) -> (rot x, c % BitSize)
4190 bool CombinerHelper::matchRotateOutOfRange(MachineInstr &MI) {
4191  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_ROTL ||
4192  MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_ROTR);
4193  unsigned Bitsize =
4194  MRI.getType(MI.getOperand(0).getReg()).getScalarSizeInBits();
4195  Register AmtReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
4196  bool OutOfRange = false;
4197  auto MatchOutOfRange = [Bitsize, &OutOfRange](const Constant *C) {
4198  if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(C))
4199  OutOfRange |= CI->getValue().uge(Bitsize);
4200  return true;
4201  };
4202  return matchUnaryPredicate(MRI, AmtReg, MatchOutOfRange) && OutOfRange;
4203 }

4205 void CombinerHelper::applyRotateOutOfRange(MachineInstr &MI) {

4207  MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_ROTR);

4209  MRI.getType(MI.getOperand(0).getReg()).getScalarSizeInBits();

4215  Observer.changingInstr(MI);
