4220 bool CombinerHelper::matchICmpToTrueFalseKnownBits(MachineInstr &MI,
4221  int64_t &MatchInfo) {
4222  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_ICMP);
4223  auto Pred = static_cast<CmpInst::Predicate>(MI.getOperand(1).getPredicate());
4224  auto KnownLHS = KB->getKnownBits(MI.getOperand(2).getReg());
4225  auto KnownRHS = KB->getKnownBits(MI.getOperand(3).getReg());
4226  std::optional<bool> KnownVal;
4227  switch (Pred) {
4228  default:
4229  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected G_ICMP predicate?");
4230  case CmpInst::ICMP_EQ:
4231  KnownVal = KnownBits::eq(KnownLHS, KnownRHS);
4232  break;
4233  case CmpInst::ICMP_NE:
4234  KnownVal = KnownBits::ne(KnownLHS, KnownRHS);
4235  break;
4236  case CmpInst::ICMP_SGE:
4237  KnownVal = KnownBits::sge(KnownLHS, KnownRHS);
4238  break;
4239  case CmpInst::ICMP_SGT:
4240  KnownVal = KnownBits::sgt(KnownLHS, KnownRHS);
4241  break;
4242  case CmpInst::ICMP_SLE:
4243  KnownVal = KnownBits::sle(KnownLHS, KnownRHS);
4244  break;
4245  case CmpInst::ICMP_SLT:
4246  KnownVal = KnownBits::slt(KnownLHS, KnownRHS);
4247  break;
4248  case CmpInst::ICMP_UGE:
4249  KnownVal = KnownBits::uge(KnownLHS, KnownRHS);
4250  break;
4251  case CmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
4252  KnownVal = KnownBits::ugt(KnownLHS, KnownRHS);
4253  break;
4254  case CmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
4255  KnownVal = KnownBits::ule(KnownLHS, KnownRHS);
4256  break;
4257  case CmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
4258  KnownVal = KnownBits::ult(KnownLHS, KnownRHS);
4259  break;
4260  }
4261  if (!KnownVal)
4262  return false;
4263  MatchInfo =
4264  *KnownVal
4265  ? getICmpTrueVal(getTargetLowering(),
4266  /*IsVector = */
4267  MRI.getType(MI.getOperand(0).getReg()).isVector(),
4268  /* IsFP = */ false)
4269  : 0;
4270  return true;
4271 }
4272 
4273 bool CombinerHelper::matchICmpToLHSKnownBits(
4274  MachineInstr &MI, std::function<void(MachineIRBuilder &)> &MatchInfo) {
4275  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_ICMP);
4276  // Given:
4277  //
4278  // %x = G_WHATEVER (... x is known to be 0 or 1 ...)
4279  // %cmp = G_ICMP ne %x, 0
4280  //
4281  // Or:
4282  //
4283  // %x = G_WHATEVER (... x is known to be 0 or 1 ...)
4284  // %cmp = G_ICMP eq %x, 1
4285  //
4286  // We can replace %cmp with %x assuming true is 1 on the target.
4287  auto Pred = static_cast<CmpInst::Predicate>(MI.getOperand(1).getPredicate());
4288  if (!CmpInst::isEquality(Pred))
4289  return false;
4290  Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
4291  LLT DstTy = MRI.getType(Dst);
4292  if (getICmpTrueVal(getTargetLowering(), DstTy.isVector(),
4293  /* IsFP = */ false) != 1)
4294  return false;
4295  int64_t OneOrZero = Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ;
4296  if (!mi_match(MI.getOperand(3).getReg(), MRI, m_SpecificICst(OneOrZero)))
4297  return false;
4298  Register LHS = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
4299  auto KnownLHS = KB->getKnownBits(LHS);
4300  if (KnownLHS.getMinValue() != 0 || KnownLHS.getMaxValue() != 1)
4301  return false;
4302  // Make sure replacing Dst with the LHS is a legal operation.
4303  LLT LHSTy = MRI.getType(LHS);
4304  unsigned LHSSize = LHSTy.getSizeInBits();
4305  unsigned DstSize = DstTy.getSizeInBits();
4306  unsigned Op = TargetOpcode::COPY;
4307  if (DstSize != LHSSize)
4308  Op = DstSize < LHSSize ? TargetOpcode::G_TRUNC : TargetOpcode::G_ZEXT;
4309  if (!isLegalOrBeforeLegalizer({Op, {DstTy, LHSTy}}))
4310  return false;
4311  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &B) { B.buildInstr(Op, {Dst}, {LHS}); };
4312  return true;
4313 }
4314 
4315 // Replace (and (or x, c1), c2) with (and x, c2) iff c1 & c2 == 0
4316 bool CombinerHelper::matchAndOrDisjointMask(
4317  MachineInstr &MI, std::function<void(MachineIRBuilder &)> &MatchInfo) {
4318  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_AND);
4319 
4320  // Ignore vector types to simplify matching the two constants.
4321  // TODO: do this for vectors and scalars via a demanded bits analysis.
4322  LLT Ty = MRI.getType(MI.getOperand(0).getReg());
4323  if (Ty.isVector())
4324  return false;
4325 
4326  Register Src;
4327  Register AndMaskReg;
4328  int64_t AndMaskBits;
4329  int64_t OrMaskBits;
4330  if (!mi_match(MI, MRI,
4331  m_GAnd(m_GOr(m_Reg(Src), m_ICst(OrMaskBits)),
4332  m_all_of(m_ICst(AndMaskBits), m_Reg(AndMaskReg)))))
4333  return false;
4334 
4335  // Check if OrMask could turn on any bits in Src.
4336  if (AndMaskBits & OrMaskBits)
4337  return false;
4338 
4339  MatchInfo = [=, &MI](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
4340  Observer.changingInstr(MI);
4341  // Canonicalize the result to have the constant on the RHS.
4342  if (MI.getOperand(1).getReg() == AndMaskReg)
4343  MI.getOperand(2).setReg(AndMaskReg);
4344  MI.getOperand(1).setReg(Src);
4345  Observer.changedInstr(MI);
4346  };
4347  return true;
4348 }
4349 
4350 /// Form a G_SBFX from a G_SEXT_INREG fed by a right shift.
4351 bool CombinerHelper::matchBitfieldExtractFromSExtInReg(
4352  MachineInstr &MI, std::function<void(MachineIRBuilder &)> &MatchInfo) {
4353  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_SEXT_INREG);
4354  Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
4355  Register Src = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
4356  LLT Ty = MRI.getType(Src);
4357  LLT ExtractTy = getTargetLowering().getPreferredShiftAmountTy(Ty);
4358  if (!LI || !LI->isLegalOrCustom({TargetOpcode::G_SBFX, {Ty, ExtractTy}}))
4359  return false;
4360  int64_t Width = MI.getOperand(2).getImm();
4361  Register ShiftSrc;
4362  int64_t ShiftImm;
4363  if (!mi_match(
4364  Src, MRI,
4365  m_OneNonDBGUse(m_any_of(m_GAShr(m_Reg(ShiftSrc), m_ICst(ShiftImm)),
4366  m_GLShr(m_Reg(ShiftSrc), m_ICst(ShiftImm))))))
4367  return false;
4368  if (ShiftImm < 0 || ShiftImm + Width > Ty.getScalarSizeInBits())
4369  return false;
4370 
4371  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
4372  auto Cst1 = B.buildConstant(ExtractTy, ShiftImm);
4373  auto Cst2 = B.buildConstant(ExtractTy, Width);
4374  B.buildSbfx(Dst, ShiftSrc, Cst1, Cst2);
4375  };
4376  return true;
4377 }
4378 
4379 /// Form a G_UBFX from "(a srl b) & mask", where b and mask are constants.
4380 bool CombinerHelper::matchBitfieldExtractFromAnd(
4381  MachineInstr &MI, std::function<void(MachineIRBuilder &)> &MatchInfo) {
4382  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_AND);
4383  Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
4384  LLT Ty = MRI.getType(Dst);
4385  LLT ExtractTy = getTargetLowering().getPreferredShiftAmountTy(Ty);
4386  if (!getTargetLowering().isConstantUnsignedBitfieldExtractLegal(
4387  TargetOpcode::G_UBFX, Ty, ExtractTy))
4388  return false;
4389 
4390  int64_t AndImm, LSBImm;
4391  Register ShiftSrc;
4392  const unsigned Size = Ty.getScalarSizeInBits();
4393  if (!mi_match(MI.getOperand(0).getReg(), MRI,
4394  m_GAnd(m_OneNonDBGUse(m_GLShr(m_Reg(ShiftSrc), m_ICst(LSBImm))),
4395  m_ICst(AndImm))))
4396  return false;
4397 
4398  // The mask is a mask of the low bits iff imm & (imm+1) == 0.
4399  auto MaybeMask = static_cast<uint64_t>(AndImm);
4400  if (MaybeMask & (MaybeMask + 1))
4401  return false;
4402 
4403  // LSB must fit within the register.
4404  if (static_cast<uint64_t>(LSBImm) >= Size)
4405  return false;
4406 
4407  uint64_t Width = APInt(Size, AndImm).countTrailingOnes();
4408  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
4409  auto WidthCst = B.buildConstant(ExtractTy, Width);
4410  auto LSBCst = B.buildConstant(ExtractTy, LSBImm);
4411  B.buildInstr(TargetOpcode::G_UBFX, {Dst}, {ShiftSrc, LSBCst, WidthCst});
4412  };
4413  return true;
4414 }
4415 
4416 bool CombinerHelper::matchBitfieldExtractFromShr(
4417  MachineInstr &MI, std::function<void(MachineIRBuilder &)> &MatchInfo) {
4418  const unsigned Opcode = MI.getOpcode();
4419  assert(Opcode == TargetOpcode::G_ASHR || Opcode == TargetOpcode::G_LSHR);
4420 
4421  const Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
4422 
4423  const unsigned ExtrOpcode = Opcode == TargetOpcode::G_ASHR
4424  ? TargetOpcode::G_SBFX
4425  : TargetOpcode::G_UBFX;
4426 
4427  // Check if the type we would use for the extract is legal
4428  LLT Ty = MRI.getType(Dst);
4429  LLT ExtractTy = getTargetLowering().getPreferredShiftAmountTy(Ty);
4430  if (!LI || !LI->isLegalOrCustom({ExtrOpcode, {Ty, ExtractTy}}))
4431  return false;
4432 
4433  Register ShlSrc;
4434  int64_t ShrAmt;
4435  int64_t ShlAmt;
4436  const unsigned Size = Ty.getScalarSizeInBits();
4437 
4438  // Try to match shr (shl x, c1), c2
4439  if (!mi_match(Dst, MRI,
4440  m_BinOp(Opcode,
4441  m_OneNonDBGUse(m_GShl(m_Reg(ShlSrc), m_ICst(ShlAmt))),
4442  m_ICst(ShrAmt))))
4443  return false;
4444 
4445  // Make sure that the shift sizes can fit a bitfield extract
4446  if (ShlAmt < 0 || ShlAmt > ShrAmt || ShrAmt >= Size)
4447  return false;
4448 
4449  // Skip this combine if the G_SEXT_INREG combine could handle it
4450  if (Opcode == TargetOpcode::G_ASHR && ShlAmt == ShrAmt)
4451  return false;
4452 
4453  // Calculate start position and width of the extract
4454  const int64_t Pos = ShrAmt - ShlAmt;
4455  const int64_t Width = Size - ShrAmt;
4456 
4457  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
4458  auto WidthCst = B.buildConstant(ExtractTy, Width);
4459  auto PosCst = B.buildConstant(ExtractTy, Pos);
4460  B.buildInstr(ExtrOpcode, {Dst}, {ShlSrc, PosCst, WidthCst});
4461  };
4462  return true;
4463 }
4464 
4465 bool CombinerHelper::matchBitfieldExtractFromShrAnd(
4466  MachineInstr &MI, std::function<void(MachineIRBuilder &)> &MatchInfo) {
4467  const unsigned Opcode = MI.getOpcode();
4468  assert(Opcode == TargetOpcode::G_LSHR || Opcode == TargetOpcode::G_ASHR);
4469 
4470  const Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
4471  LLT Ty = MRI.getType(Dst);
4472  LLT ExtractTy = getTargetLowering().getPreferredShiftAmountTy(Ty);
4473  if (!getTargetLowering().isConstantUnsignedBitfieldExtractLegal(
4474  TargetOpcode::G_UBFX, Ty, ExtractTy))
4475  return false;
4476 
4477  // Try to match shr (and x, c1), c2
4478  Register AndSrc;
4479  int64_t ShrAmt;
4480  int64_t SMask;
4481  if (!mi_match(Dst, MRI,
4482  m_BinOp(Opcode,
4483  m_OneNonDBGUse(m_GAnd(m_Reg(AndSrc), m_ICst(SMask))),
4484  m_ICst(ShrAmt))))
4485  return false;
4486 
4487  const unsigned Size = Ty.getScalarSizeInBits();
4488  if (ShrAmt < 0 || ShrAmt >= Size)
4489  return false;
4490 
4491  // If the shift subsumes the mask, emit the 0 directly.
4492  if (0 == (SMask >> ShrAmt)) {
4493  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
4494  B.buildConstant(Dst, 0);
4495  };
4496  return true;
4497  }
4498 
4499  // Check that ubfx can do the extraction, with no holes in the mask.
4500  uint64_t UMask = SMask;
4501  UMask |= maskTrailingOnes<uint64_t>(ShrAmt);
4502  UMask &= maskTrailingOnes<uint64_t>(Size);
4503  if (!isMask_64(UMask))
4504  return false;
4505 
4506  // Calculate start position and width of the extract.
4507  const int64_t Pos = ShrAmt;
4508  const int64_t Width = llvm::countr_one(UMask) - ShrAmt;
4509 
4510  // It's preferable to keep the shift, rather than form G_SBFX.
4511  // TODO: remove the G_AND via demanded bits analysis.
4512  if (Opcode == TargetOpcode::G_ASHR && Width + ShrAmt == Size)
4513  return false;
4514 
4515  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
4516  auto WidthCst = B.buildConstant(ExtractTy, Width);
4517  auto PosCst = B.buildConstant(ExtractTy, Pos);
4518  B.buildInstr(TargetOpcode::G_UBFX, {Dst}, {AndSrc, PosCst, WidthCst});
4519  };
4520  return true;
4521 }
4522 
4523 bool CombinerHelper::reassociationCanBreakAddressingModePattern(
4524  MachineInstr &PtrAdd) {
4525  assert(PtrAdd.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_PTR_ADD);
4526 
4527  Register Src1Reg = PtrAdd.getOperand(1).getReg();
4528  MachineInstr *Src1Def = getOpcodeDef(TargetOpcode::G_PTR_ADD, Src1Reg, MRI);
4529  if (!Src1Def)
4530  return false;
4531 
4532  Register Src2Reg = PtrAdd.getOperand(2).getReg();
4533 
4534  if (MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(Src1Reg))
4535  return false;
4536 
4537  auto C1 = getIConstantVRegVal(Src1Def->getOperand(2).getReg(), MRI);
4538  if (!C1)
4539  return false;
4540  auto C2 = getIConstantVRegVal(Src2Reg, MRI);
4541  if (!C2)
4542  return false;
4543 
4544  const APInt &C1APIntVal = *C1;
4545  const APInt &C2APIntVal = *C2;
4546  const int64_t CombinedValue = (C1APIntVal + C2APIntVal).getSExtValue();
4547 
4548  for (auto &UseMI : MRI.use_nodbg_instructions(Src1Reg)) {
4549  // This combine may end up running before ptrtoint/inttoptr combines
4550  // manage to eliminate redundant conversions, so try to look through them.
4551  MachineInstr *ConvUseMI = &UseMI;
4552  unsigned ConvUseOpc = ConvUseMI->getOpcode();
4553  while (ConvUseOpc == TargetOpcode::G_INTTOPTR ||
4554  ConvUseOpc == TargetOpcode::G_PTRTOINT) {
4555  Register DefReg = ConvUseMI->getOperand(0).getReg();
4556  if (!MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(DefReg))
4557  break;
4558  ConvUseMI = &*MRI.use_instr_nodbg_begin(DefReg);
4559  ConvUseOpc = ConvUseMI->getOpcode();
4560  }
4561  auto LoadStore = ConvUseOpc == TargetOpcode::G_LOAD ||
4562  ConvUseOpc == TargetOpcode::G_STORE;
4563  if (!LoadStore)
4564  continue;
4565  // Is x[offset2] already not a legal addressing mode? If so then
4566  // reassociating the constants breaks nothing (we test offset2 because
4567  // that's the one we hope to fold into the load or store).
4568  TargetLoweringBase::AddrMode AM;
4569  AM.HasBaseReg = true;
4570  AM.BaseOffs = C2APIntVal.getSExtValue();
4571  unsigned AS =
4572  MRI.getType(ConvUseMI->getOperand(1).getReg()).getAddressSpace();
4573  Type *AccessTy =
4574  getTypeForLLT(MRI.getType(ConvUseMI->getOperand(0).getReg()),
4575  PtrAdd.getMF()->getFunction().getContext());
4576  const auto &TLI = *PtrAdd.getMF()->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering();
4577  if (!TLI.isLegalAddressingMode(PtrAdd.getMF()->getDataLayout(), AM,
4578  AccessTy, AS))
4579  continue;
4580 
4581  // Would x[offset1+offset2] still be a legal addressing mode?
4582  AM.BaseOffs = CombinedValue;
4583  if (!TLI.isLegalAddressingMode(PtrAdd.getMF()->getDataLayout(), AM,
4584  AccessTy, AS))
4585  return true;
4586  }
4587 
4588  return false;
4589 }
4590 
4591 bool CombinerHelper::matchReassocConstantInnerRHS(GPtrAdd &MI,
4592  MachineInstr *RHS,
4593  BuildFnTy &MatchInfo) {
4594  // G_PTR_ADD(BASE, G_ADD(X, C)) -> G_PTR_ADD(G_PTR_ADD(BASE, X), C)
4595  Register Src1Reg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
4596  if (RHS->getOpcode() != TargetOpcode::G_ADD)
4597  return false;
4598  auto C2 = getIConstantVRegVal(RHS->getOperand(2).getReg(), MRI);
4599  if (!C2)
4600  return false;
4601 
4602  MatchInfo = [=, &MI](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
4603  LLT PtrTy = MRI.getType(MI.getOperand(0).getReg());
4604 
4605  auto NewBase =
4606  Builder.buildPtrAdd(PtrTy, Src1Reg, RHS->getOperand(1).getReg());
4607  Observer.changingInstr(MI);
4608  MI.getOperand(1).setReg(NewBase.getReg(0));
4609  MI.getOperand(2).setReg(RHS->getOperand(2).getReg());
4610  Observer.changedInstr(MI);
4611  };
4612  return !reassociationCanBreakAddressingModePattern(MI);
4613 }
4614 
4615 bool CombinerHelper::matchReassocConstantInnerLHS(GPtrAdd &MI,
4616  MachineInstr *LHS,
4617  MachineInstr *RHS,
4618  BuildFnTy &MatchInfo) {
4619  // G_PTR_ADD (G_PTR_ADD X, C), Y) -> (G_PTR_ADD (G_PTR_ADD(X, Y), C)
4620  // if and only if (G_PTR_ADD X, C) has one use.
4621  Register LHSBase;
4622  std::optional<ValueAndVReg> LHSCstOff;
4623  if (!mi_match(MI.getBaseReg(), MRI,
4624  m_OneNonDBGUse(m_GPtrAdd(m_Reg(LHSBase), m_GCst(LHSCstOff)))))
4625  return false;
4626 
4627  auto *LHSPtrAdd = cast<GPtrAdd>(LHS);
4628  MatchInfo = [=, &MI](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
4629  // When we change LHSPtrAdd's offset register we might cause it to use a reg
4630  // before its def. Sink the instruction so the outer PTR_ADD to ensure this
4631  // doesn't happen.
4632  LHSPtrAdd->moveBefore(&MI);
4633  Register RHSReg = MI.getOffsetReg();
4634  // set VReg will cause type mismatch if it comes from extend/trunc
4635  auto NewCst = B.buildConstant(MRI.getType(RHSReg), LHSCstOff->Value);
4636  Observer.changingInstr(MI);
4637  MI.getOperand(2).setReg(NewCst.getReg(0));
4638  Observer.changedInstr(MI);
4639  Observer.changingInstr(*LHSPtrAdd);
4640  LHSPtrAdd->getOperand(2).setReg(RHSReg);
4641  Observer.changedInstr(*LHSPtrAdd);
4642  };
4643  return !reassociationCanBreakAddressingModePattern(MI);
4644 }
4645 
4646 bool CombinerHelper::matchReassocFoldConstantsInSubTree(GPtrAdd &MI,
4647  MachineInstr *LHS,
4648  MachineInstr *RHS,
4649  BuildFnTy &MatchInfo) {
4650  // G_PTR_ADD(G_PTR_ADD(BASE, C1), C2) -> G_PTR_ADD(BASE, C1+C2)
4651  auto *LHSPtrAdd = dyn_cast<GPtrAdd>(LHS);
4652  if (!LHSPtrAdd)
4653  return false;
4654 
4655  Register Src2Reg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
4656  Register LHSSrc1 = LHSPtrAdd->getBaseReg();
4657  Register LHSSrc2 = LHSPtrAdd->getOffsetReg();
4658  auto C1 = getIConstantVRegVal(LHSSrc2, MRI);
4659  if (!C1)
4660  return false;
4661  auto C2 = getIConstantVRegVal(Src2Reg, MRI);
4662  if (!C2)
4663  return false;
4664 
4665  MatchInfo = [=, &MI](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
4666  auto NewCst = B.buildConstant(MRI.getType(Src2Reg), *C1 + *C2);
4667  Observer.changingInstr(MI);
4668  MI.getOperand(1).setReg(LHSSrc1);
4669  MI.getOperand(2).setReg(NewCst.getReg(0));
4670  Observer.changedInstr(MI);
4671  };
4672  return !reassociationCanBreakAddressingModePattern(MI);
4673 }
4674 
4675 bool CombinerHelper::matchReassocPtrAdd(MachineInstr &MI,
4676  BuildFnTy &MatchInfo) {
4677  auto &PtrAdd = cast<GPtrAdd>(MI);
4678  // We're trying to match a few pointer computation patterns here for
4679  // re-association opportunities.
4680  // 1) Isolating a constant operand to be on the RHS, e.g.:
4681  // G_PTR_ADD(BASE, G_ADD(X, C)) -> G_PTR_ADD(G_PTR_ADD(BASE, X), C)
4682  //
4683  // 2) Folding two constants in each sub-tree as long as such folding
4684  // doesn't break a legal addressing mode.
4685  // G_PTR_ADD(G_PTR_ADD(BASE, C1), C2) -> G_PTR_ADD(BASE, C1+C2)
4686  //
4687  // 3) Move a constant from the LHS of an inner op to the RHS of the outer.
4688  // G_PTR_ADD (G_PTR_ADD X, C), Y) -> G_PTR_ADD (G_PTR_ADD(X, Y), C)
4689  // iif (G_PTR_ADD X, C) has one use.
4690  MachineInstr *LHS = MRI.getVRegDef(PtrAdd.getBaseReg());
4691  MachineInstr *RHS = MRI.getVRegDef(PtrAdd.getOffsetReg());
4692 
4693  // Try to match example 2.
4694  if (matchReassocFoldConstantsInSubTree(PtrAdd, LHS, RHS, MatchInfo))
4695  return true;
4696 
4697  // Try to match example 3.
4698  if (matchReassocConstantInnerLHS(PtrAdd, LHS, RHS, MatchInfo))
4699  return true;
4700 
4701  // Try to match example 1.
4702  if (matchReassocConstantInnerRHS(PtrAdd, RHS, MatchInfo))
4703  return true;
4704 
4705  return false;
4706 }
4707 
4708 bool CombinerHelper::matchConstantFold(MachineInstr &MI, APInt &MatchInfo) {
4709  Register Op1 = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
4710  Register Op2 = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
4711  auto MaybeCst = ConstantFoldBinOp(MI.getOpcode(), Op1, Op2, MRI);
4712  if (!MaybeCst)
4713  return false;
4714  MatchInfo = *MaybeCst;
4715  return true;
4716 }
4717 
4718 bool CombinerHelper::matchNarrowBinopFeedingAnd(
4719  MachineInstr &MI, std::function<void(MachineIRBuilder &)> &MatchInfo) {
4720  // Look for a binop feeding into an AND with a mask:
4721  //
4722  // %add = G_ADD %lhs, %rhs
4723  // %and = G_AND %add, 000...11111111
4724  //
4725  // Check if it's possible to perform the binop at a narrower width and zext
4726  // back to the original width like so:
4727  //
4728  // %narrow_lhs = G_TRUNC %lhs
4729  // %narrow_rhs = G_TRUNC %rhs
4730  // %narrow_add = G_ADD %narrow_lhs, %narrow_rhs
4731  // %new_add = G_ZEXT %narrow_add
4732  // %and = G_AND %new_add, 000...11111111
4733  //
4734  // This can allow later combines to eliminate the G_AND if it turns out
4735  // that the mask is irrelevant.
4736  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_AND);
4737  Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
4738  Register AndLHS = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
4739  Register AndRHS = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
4740  LLT WideTy = MRI.getType(Dst);
4741 
4742  // If the potential binop has more than one use, then it's possible that one
4743  // of those uses will need its full width.
4744  if (!WideTy.isScalar() || !MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(AndLHS))
4745  return false;
4746 
4747  // Check if the LHS feeding the AND is impacted by the high bits that we're
4748  // masking out.
4749  //
4750  // e.g. for 64-bit x, y:
4751  //
4752  // add_64(x, y) & 65535 == zext(add_16(trunc(x), trunc(y))) & 65535
4753  MachineInstr *LHSInst = getDefIgnoringCopies(AndLHS, MRI);
4754  if (!LHSInst)
4755  return false;
4756  unsigned LHSOpc = LHSInst->getOpcode();
4757  switch (LHSOpc) {
4758  default:
4759  return false;
4760  case TargetOpcode::G_ADD:
4761  case TargetOpcode::G_SUB:
4762  case TargetOpcode::G_MUL:
4763  case TargetOpcode::G_AND:
4764  case TargetOpcode::G_OR:
4765  case TargetOpcode::G_XOR:
4766  break;
4767  }
4768 
4769  // Find the mask on the RHS.
4770  auto Cst = getIConstantVRegValWithLookThrough(AndRHS, MRI);
4771  if (!Cst)
4772  return false;
4773  auto Mask = Cst->Value;
4774  if (!Mask.isMask())
4775  return false;
4776 
4777  // No point in combining if there's nothing to truncate.
4778  unsigned NarrowWidth = Mask.countTrailingOnes();
4779  if (NarrowWidth == WideTy.getSizeInBits())
4780  return false;
4781  LLT NarrowTy = LLT::scalar(NarrowWidth);
4782 
4783  // Check if adding the zext + truncates could be harmful.
4784  auto &MF = *MI.getMF();
4785  const auto &TLI = getTargetLowering();
4786  LLVMContext &Ctx = MF.getFunction().getContext();
4787  auto &DL = MF.getDataLayout();
4788  if (!TLI.isTruncateFree(WideTy, NarrowTy, DL, Ctx) ||
4789  !TLI.isZExtFree(NarrowTy, WideTy, DL, Ctx))
4790  return false;
4791  if (!isLegalOrBeforeLegalizer({TargetOpcode::G_TRUNC, {NarrowTy, WideTy}}) ||
4792  !isLegalOrBeforeLegalizer({TargetOpcode::G_ZEXT, {WideTy, NarrowTy}}))
4793  return false;
4794  Register BinOpLHS = LHSInst->getOperand(1).getReg();
4795  Register BinOpRHS = LHSInst->getOperand(2).getReg();
4796  MatchInfo = [=, &MI](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
4797  auto NarrowLHS = Builder.buildTrunc(NarrowTy, BinOpLHS);
4798  auto NarrowRHS = Builder.buildTrunc(NarrowTy, BinOpRHS);
4799  auto NarrowBinOp =
4800  Builder.buildInstr(LHSOpc, {NarrowTy}, {NarrowLHS, NarrowRHS});
4801  auto Ext = Builder.buildZExt(WideTy, NarrowBinOp);
4802  Observer.changingInstr(MI);
4803  MI.getOperand(1).setReg(Ext.getReg(0));
4804  Observer.changedInstr(MI);
4805  };
4806  return true;
4807 }
4808 
4809 bool CombinerHelper::matchMulOBy2(MachineInstr &MI, BuildFnTy &MatchInfo) {
4810  unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode();
4811  assert(Opc == TargetOpcode::G_UMULO || Opc == TargetOpcode::G_SMULO);
4812 
4813  if (!mi_match(MI.getOperand(3).getReg(), MRI, m_SpecificICstOrSplat(2)))
4814  return false;
4815 
4816  MatchInfo = [=, &MI](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
4817  Observer.changingInstr(MI);
4818  unsigned NewOpc = Opc == TargetOpcode::G_UMULO ? TargetOpcode::G_UADDO
4819  : TargetOpcode::G_SADDO;
4820  MI.setDesc(Builder.getTII().get(NewOpc));
4821  MI.getOperand(3).setReg(MI.getOperand(2).getReg());
4822  Observer.changedInstr(MI);
4823  };
4824  return true;
4825 }
4826 
4827 bool CombinerHelper::matchMulOBy0(MachineInstr &MI, BuildFnTy &MatchInfo) {
4828  // (G_*MULO x, 0) -> 0 + no carry out
4829  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_UMULO ||
4830  MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_SMULO);
4831  if (!mi_match(MI.getOperand(3).getReg(), MRI, m_SpecificICstOrSplat(0)))
4832  return false;
4833  Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
4834  Register Carry = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
4835  if (!isConstantLegalOrBeforeLegalizer(MRI.getType(Dst)) ||
4836  !isConstantLegalOrBeforeLegalizer(MRI.getType(Carry)))
4837  return false;
4838  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
4839  B.buildConstant(Dst, 0);
4840  B.buildConstant(Carry, 0);
4841  };
4842  return true;
4843 }
4844 
4845 bool CombinerHelper::matchAddOBy0(MachineInstr &MI, BuildFnTy &MatchInfo) {
4846  // (G_*ADDO x, 0) -> x + no carry out
4847  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_UADDO ||
4848  MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_SADDO);
4849  if (!mi_match(MI.getOperand(3).getReg(), MRI, m_SpecificICstOrSplat(0)))
4850  return false;
4851  Register Carry = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
4852  if (!isConstantLegalOrBeforeLegalizer(MRI.getType(Carry)))
4853  return false;
4854  Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
4855  Register LHS = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
4856  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
4857  B.buildCopy(Dst, LHS);
4858  B.buildConstant(Carry, 0);
4859  };
4860  return true;
4861 }
4862 
4863 bool CombinerHelper::matchAddEToAddO(MachineInstr &MI, BuildFnTy &MatchInfo) {
4864  // (G_*ADDE x, y, 0) -> (G_*ADDO x, y)
4865  // (G_*SUBE x, y, 0) -> (G_*SUBO x, y)
4866  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_UADDE ||
4867  MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_SADDE ||
4868  MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_USUBE ||
4869  MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_SSUBE);
4870  if (!mi_match(MI.getOperand(4).getReg(), MRI, m_SpecificICstOrSplat(0)))
4871  return false;
4872  MatchInfo = [&](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
4873  unsigned NewOpcode;
4874  switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
4875  case TargetOpcode::G_UADDE:
4876  NewOpcode = TargetOpcode::G_UADDO;
4877  break;
4878  case TargetOpcode::G_SADDE:
4879  NewOpcode = TargetOpcode::G_SADDO;
4880  break;
4881  case TargetOpcode::G_USUBE:
4882  NewOpcode = TargetOpcode::G_USUBO;
4883  break;
4884  case TargetOpcode::G_SSUBE:
4885  NewOpcode = TargetOpcode::G_SSUBO;
4886  break;
4887  }
4888  Observer.changingInstr(MI);
4889  MI.setDesc(B.getTII().get(NewOpcode));
4890  MI.removeOperand(4);
4891  Observer.changedInstr(MI);
4892  };
4893  return true;
4894 }
4895 
4896 bool CombinerHelper::matchSubAddSameReg(MachineInstr &MI,
4897  BuildFnTy &MatchInfo) {
4898  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_SUB);
4899  Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
4900  // (x + y) - z -> x (if y == z)
4901  // (x + y) - z -> y (if x == z)
4902  Register X, Y, Z;
4903  if (mi_match(Dst, MRI, m_GSub(m_GAdd(m_Reg(X), m_Reg(Y)), m_Reg(Z)))) {
4904  Register ReplaceReg;
4905  int64_t CstX, CstY;
4906  if (Y == Z || (mi_match(Y, MRI, m_ICstOrSplat(CstY)) &&
4907  mi_match(Z, MRI, m_SpecificICstOrSplat(CstY))))
4908  ReplaceReg = X;
4909  else if (X == Z || (mi_match(X, MRI, m_ICstOrSplat(CstX)) &&
4910  mi_match(Z, MRI, m_SpecificICstOrSplat(CstX))))
4911  ReplaceReg = Y;
4912  if (ReplaceReg) {
4913  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &B) { B.buildCopy(Dst, ReplaceReg); };
4914  return true;
4915  }
4916  }
4917 
4918  // x - (y + z) -> 0 - y (if x == z)
4919  // x - (y + z) -> 0 - z (if x == y)
4920  if (mi_match(Dst, MRI, m_GSub(m_Reg(X), m_GAdd(m_Reg(Y), m_Reg(Z))))) {
4921  Register ReplaceReg;
4922  int64_t CstX;
4923  if (X == Z || (mi_match(X, MRI, m_ICstOrSplat(CstX)) &&
4924  mi_match(Z, MRI, m_SpecificICstOrSplat(CstX))))
4925  ReplaceReg = Y;
4926  else if (X == Y || (mi_match(X, MRI, m_ICstOrSplat(CstX)) &&
4927  mi_match(Y, MRI, m_SpecificICstOrSplat(CstX))))
4928  ReplaceReg = Z;
4929  if (ReplaceReg) {
4930  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
4931  auto Zero = B.buildConstant(MRI.getType(Dst), 0);
4932  B.buildSub(Dst, Zero, ReplaceReg);
4933  };
4934  return true;
4935  }
4936  }
4937  return false;
4938 }
4939 
4940 MachineInstr *CombinerHelper::buildUDivUsingMul(MachineInstr &MI) {
4941  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_UDIV);
4942  auto &UDiv = cast<GenericMachineInstr>(MI);
4943  Register Dst = UDiv.getReg(0);
4944  Register LHS = UDiv.getReg(1);
4945  Register RHS = UDiv.getReg(2);
4946  LLT Ty = MRI.getType(Dst);
4947  LLT ScalarTy = Ty.getScalarType();
4948  const unsigned EltBits = ScalarTy.getScalarSizeInBits();
4949  LLT ShiftAmtTy = getTargetLowering().getPreferredShiftAmountTy(Ty);
4950  LLT ScalarShiftAmtTy = ShiftAmtTy.getScalarType();
4951  auto &MIB = Builder;
4952  MIB.setInstrAndDebugLoc(MI);
4953 
4954  bool UseNPQ = false;
4955  SmallVector<Register, 16> PreShifts, PostShifts, MagicFactors, NPQFactors;
4956 
4957  auto BuildUDIVPattern = [&](const Constant *C) {
4958  auto *CI = cast<ConstantInt>(C);
4959  const APInt &Divisor = CI->getValue();
4960 
4961  bool SelNPQ = false;
4962  APInt Magic(Divisor.getBitWidth(), 0);
4963  unsigned PreShift = 0, PostShift = 0;
4964 
4965  // Magic algorithm doesn't work for division by 1. We need to emit a select
4966  // at the end.
4967  // TODO: Use undef values for divisor of 1.
4968  if (!Divisor.isOneValue()) {
4969  UnsignedDivisionByConstantInfo magics =
4970  UnsignedDivisionByConstantInfo::get(Divisor);
4971 
4972  Magic = std::move(magics.Magic);
4973 
4974  assert(magics.PreShift < Divisor.getBitWidth() &&
4975  "We shouldn't generate an undefined shift!");
4976  assert(magics.PostShift < Divisor.getBitWidth() &&
4977  "We shouldn't generate an undefined shift!");
4978  assert((!magics.IsAdd || magics.PreShift == 0) && "Unexpected pre-shift");
4979  PreShift = magics.PreShift;
4980  PostShift = magics.PostShift;
4981  SelNPQ = magics.IsAdd;
4982  }
4983 
4984  PreShifts.push_back(
4985  MIB.buildConstant(ScalarShiftAmtTy, PreShift).getReg(0));
4986  MagicFactors.push_back(MIB.buildConstant(ScalarTy, Magic).getReg(0));
4987  NPQFactors.push_back(
4988  MIB.buildConstant(ScalarTy,
4989  SelNPQ ? APInt::getOneBitSet(EltBits, EltBits - 1)
4990  : APInt::getZero(EltBits))
4991  .getReg(0));
4992  PostShifts.push_back(
4993  MIB.buildConstant(ScalarShiftAmtTy, PostShift).getReg(0));
4994  UseNPQ |= SelNPQ;
4995  return true;
4996  };
4997 
4998  // Collect the shifts/magic values from each element.
4999  bool Matched = matchUnaryPredicate(MRI, RHS, BuildUDIVPattern);
5000  (void)Matched;
5001  assert(Matched && "Expected unary predicate match to succeed");
5002 
5003  Register PreShift, PostShift, MagicFactor, NPQFactor;
5004  auto *RHSDef = getOpcodeDef<GBuildVector>(RHS, MRI);
5005  if (RHSDef) {
5006  PreShift = MIB.buildBuildVector(ShiftAmtTy, PreShifts).getReg(0);
5007  MagicFactor = MIB.buildBuildVector(Ty, MagicFactors).getReg(0);
5008  NPQFactor = MIB.buildBuildVector(Ty, NPQFactors).getReg(0);
5009  PostShift = MIB.buildBuildVector(ShiftAmtTy, PostShifts).getReg(0);
5010  } else {
5011  assert(MRI.getType(RHS).isScalar() &&
5012  "Non-build_vector operation should have been a scalar");
5013  PreShift = PreShifts[0];
5014  MagicFactor = MagicFactors[0];
5015  PostShift = PostShifts[0];
5016  }
5017 
5018  Register Q = LHS;
5019  Q = MIB.buildLShr(Ty, Q, PreShift).getReg(0);
5020 
5021  // Multiply the numerator (operand 0) by the magic value.
5022  Q = MIB.buildUMulH(Ty, Q, MagicFactor).getReg(0);
5023 
5024  if (UseNPQ) {
5025  Register NPQ = MIB.buildSub(Ty, LHS, Q).getReg(0);
5026 
5027  // For vectors we might have a mix of non-NPQ/NPQ paths, so use
5028  // G_UMULH to act as a SRL-by-1 for NPQ, else multiply by zero.
5029  if (Ty.isVector())
5030  NPQ = MIB.buildUMulH(Ty, NPQ, NPQFactor).getReg(0);
5031  else
5032  NPQ = MIB.buildLShr(Ty, NPQ, MIB.buildConstant(ShiftAmtTy, 1)).getReg(0);
5033 
5034  Q = MIB.buildAdd(Ty, NPQ, Q).getReg(0);
5035  }
5036 
5037  Q = MIB.buildLShr(Ty, Q, PostShift).getReg(0);
5038  auto One = MIB.buildConstant(Ty, 1);
5039  auto IsOne = MIB.buildICmp(
5040  CmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_EQ,
5041  Ty.isScalar() ? LLT::scalar(1) : Ty.changeElementSize(1), RHS, One);
5042  return MIB.buildSelect(Ty, IsOne, LHS, Q);
5043 }
5044 
5045 bool CombinerHelper::matchUDivByConst(MachineInstr &MI) {
5046  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_UDIV);
5047  Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
5048  Register RHS = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
5049  LLT DstTy = MRI.getType(Dst);
5050  auto *RHSDef = MRI.getVRegDef(RHS);
5051  if (!isConstantOrConstantVector(*RHSDef, MRI))
5052  return false;
5053 
5054  auto &MF = *MI.getMF();
5055  AttributeList Attr = MF.getFunction().getAttributes();
5056  const auto &TLI = getTargetLowering();
5057  LLVMContext &Ctx = MF.getFunction().getContext();
5058  auto &DL = MF.getDataLayout();
5059  if (TLI.isIntDivCheap(getApproximateEVTForLLT(DstTy, DL, Ctx), Attr))
5060  return false;
5061 
5062  // Don't do this for minsize because the instruction sequence is usually
5063  // larger.
5064  if (MF.getFunction().hasMinSize())
5065  return false;
5066 
5067  // Don't do this if the types are not going to be legal.
5068  if (LI) {
5069  if (!isLegalOrBeforeLegalizer({TargetOpcode::G_MUL, {DstTy, DstTy}}))
5070  return false;
5071  if (!isLegalOrBeforeLegalizer({TargetOpcode::G_UMULH, {DstTy}}))
5072  return false;
5073  if (!isLegalOrBeforeLegalizer(
5074  {TargetOpcode::G_ICMP,
5075  {DstTy.isVector() ? DstTy.changeElementSize(1) : LLT::scalar(1),
5076  DstTy}}))
5077  return false;
5078  }
5079 
5080  auto CheckEltValue = [&](const Constant *C) {
5081  if (auto *CI = dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantInt>(C))
5082  return !CI->isZero();
5083  return false;
5084  };
5085  return matchUnaryPredicate(MRI, RHS, CheckEltValue);
5086 }
5087 
5088 void CombinerHelper::applyUDivByConst(MachineInstr &MI) {
5089  auto *NewMI = buildUDivUsingMul(MI);
5090  replaceSingleDefInstWithReg(MI, NewMI->getOperand(0).getReg());
5091 }

5093 bool CombinerHelper::matchSDivByConst(MachineInstr &MI) {
5094  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_SDIV && "Expected SDIV");
5095  Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
5096  Register RHS = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
5097  LLT DstTy = MRI.getType(Dst);
5098 
5099  auto &MF = *MI.getMF();
5100  AttributeList Attr = MF.getFunction().getAttributes();
5101  const auto &TLI = getTargetLowering();
5102  LLVMContext &Ctx = MF.getFunction().getContext();
5103  auto &DL = MF.getDataLayout();
5104  if (TLI.isIntDivCheap(getApproximateEVTForLLT(DstTy, DL, Ctx), Attr))
5105  return false;
5106 
5107  // Don't do this for minsize because the instruction sequence is usually
5108  // larger.
5109  if (MF.getFunction().hasMinSize())
5110  return false;
5111 
5112  // If the sdiv has an 'exact' flag we can use a simpler lowering.
5113  if (MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::MIFlag::IsExact)) {
5114  return matchUnaryPredicate(
5115  MRI, RHS, [](const Constant *C) { return C && !C->isZeroValue(); });
5116  }
5117 
5118  // Don't support the general case for now.
5119  return false;
5120 }

5124  replaceSingleDefInstWithReg(MI, NewMI->getOperand(0).getReg());

5126 
5127 MachineInstr *CombinerHelper::buildSDivUsingMul(MachineInstr &MI) {
5128  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_SDIV && "Expected SDIV");
5129  auto &SDiv = cast<GenericMachineInstr>(MI);
5130  Register Dst = SDiv.getReg(0);
5131  Register LHS = SDiv.getReg(1);
5132  Register RHS = SDiv.getReg(2);
5133  LLT Ty = MRI.getType(Dst);
5134  LLT ScalarTy = Ty.getScalarType();
5135  LLT ShiftAmtTy = getTargetLowering().getPreferredShiftAmountTy(Ty);
5136  LLT ScalarShiftAmtTy = ShiftAmtTy.getScalarType();
5137  auto &MIB = Builder;
5138  MIB.setInstrAndDebugLoc(MI);
5139 
5140  bool UseSRA = false;
5141  SmallVector<Register, 16> Shifts, Factors;
5142 
5143  auto *RHSDef = cast<GenericMachineInstr>(getDefIgnoringCopies(RHS, MRI));
5144  bool IsSplat = getIConstantSplatVal(*RHSDef, MRI).has_value();
5145 
5146  auto BuildSDIVPattern = [&](const Constant *C) {
5147  // Don't recompute inverses for each splat element.
5148  if (IsSplat && !Factors.empty()) {
5149  Shifts.push_back(Shifts[0]);
5150  Factors.push_back(Factors[0]);
5151  return true;
5152  }
5153 
5154  auto *CI = cast<ConstantInt>(C);
5155  APInt Divisor = CI->getValue();
5156  unsigned Shift = Divisor.countTrailingZeros();
5157  if (Shift) {
5158  Divisor.ashrInPlace(Shift);
5159  UseSRA = true;
5160  }
5161 
5162  // Calculate the multiplicative inverse modulo BW.
5163  // 2^W requires W + 1 bits, so we have to extend and then truncate.
5164  unsigned W = Divisor.getBitWidth();
5165  APInt Factor = Divisor.zext(W + 1)
5166  .multiplicativeInverse(APInt::getSignedMinValue(W + 1))
5167  .trunc(W);
5168  Shifts.push_back(MIB.buildConstant(ScalarShiftAmtTy, Shift).getReg(0));
5169  Factors.push_back(MIB.buildConstant(ScalarTy, Factor).getReg(0));
5170  return true;
5171  };
5172 
5173  // Collect all magic values from the build vector.
5174  bool Matched = matchUnaryPredicate(MRI, RHS, BuildSDIVPattern);
5175  (void)Matched;
5176  assert(Matched && "Expected unary predicate match to succeed");
5177 
5178  Register Shift, Factor;
5179  if (Ty.isVector()) {
5180  Shift = MIB.buildBuildVector(ShiftAmtTy, Shifts).getReg(0);
5181  Factor = MIB.buildBuildVector(Ty, Factors).getReg(0);
5182  } else {
5183  Shift = Shifts[0];
5184  Factor = Factors[0];
5185  }
5186 
5187  Register Res = LHS;
5188 
5189  if (UseSRA)
5190  Res = MIB.buildAShr(Ty, Res, Shift, MachineInstr::IsExact).getReg(0);
5191 
5192  return MIB.buildMul(Ty, Res, Factor);
5193 }
5194 
5195 bool CombinerHelper::matchUMulHToLShr(MachineInstr &MI) {
5196  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_UMULH);
5197  Register RHS = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
5198  Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
5199  LLT Ty = MRI.getType(Dst);
5200  LLT ShiftAmtTy = getTargetLowering().getPreferredShiftAmountTy(Ty);
5201  auto MatchPow2ExceptOne = [&](const Constant *C) {
5202  if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(C))
5203  return CI->getValue().isPowerOf2() && !CI->getValue().isOne();
5204  return false;
5205  };
5206  if (!matchUnaryPredicate(MRI, RHS, MatchPow2ExceptOne, false))
5207  return false;
5208  return isLegalOrBeforeLegalizer({TargetOpcode::G_LSHR, {Ty, ShiftAmtTy}});
5209 }
5210 
5211 void CombinerHelper::applyUMulHToLShr(MachineInstr &MI) {
5212  Register LHS = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
5213  Register RHS = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
5214  Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
5215  LLT Ty = MRI.getType(Dst);
5216  LLT ShiftAmtTy = getTargetLowering().getPreferredShiftAmountTy(Ty);
5217  unsigned NumEltBits = Ty.getScalarSizeInBits();
5218 
5219  Builder.setInstrAndDebugLoc(MI);
5220  auto LogBase2 = buildLogBase2(RHS, Builder);
5221  auto ShiftAmt =
5222  Builder.buildSub(Ty, Builder.buildConstant(Ty, NumEltBits), LogBase2);
5223  auto Trunc = Builder.buildZExtOrTrunc(ShiftAmtTy, ShiftAmt);
5224  Builder.buildLShr(Dst, LHS, Trunc);
5225  MI.eraseFromParent();
5226 }
5227 
5228 bool CombinerHelper::matchRedundantNegOperands(MachineInstr &MI,
5229  BuildFnTy &MatchInfo) {
5230  unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode();
5231  assert(Opc == TargetOpcode::G_FADD || Opc == TargetOpcode::G_FSUB ||
5232  Opc == TargetOpcode::G_FMUL || Opc == TargetOpcode::G_FDIV ||
5233  Opc == TargetOpcode::G_FMAD || Opc == TargetOpcode::G_FMA);
5234 
5235  Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
5236  Register X = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
5237  Register Y = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
5238  LLT Type = MRI.getType(Dst);
5239 
5240  // fold (fadd x, fneg(y)) -> (fsub x, y)
5241  // fold (fadd fneg(y), x) -> (fsub x, y)
5242  // G_ADD is commutative so both cases are checked by m_GFAdd
5243  if (mi_match(Dst, MRI, m_GFAdd(m_Reg(X), m_GFNeg(m_Reg(Y)))) &&
5244  isLegalOrBeforeLegalizer({TargetOpcode::G_FSUB, {Type}})) {
5245  Opc = TargetOpcode::G_FSUB;
5246  }
5247  /// fold (fsub x, fneg(y)) -> (fadd x, y)
5248  else if (mi_match(Dst, MRI, m_GFSub(m_Reg(X), m_GFNeg(m_Reg(Y)))) &&
5249  isLegalOrBeforeLegalizer({TargetOpcode::G_FADD, {Type}})) {
5250  Opc = TargetOpcode::G_FADD;
5251  }
5252  // fold (fmul fneg(x), fneg(y)) -> (fmul x, y)
5253  // fold (fdiv fneg(x), fneg(y)) -> (fdiv x, y)
5254  // fold (fmad fneg(x), fneg(y), z) -> (fmad x, y, z)
5255  // fold (fma fneg(x), fneg(y), z) -> (fma x, y, z)
5256  else if ((Opc == TargetOpcode::G_FMUL || Opc == TargetOpcode::G_FDIV ||
5257  Opc == TargetOpcode::G_FMAD || Opc == TargetOpcode::G_FMA) &&
5258  mi_match(X, MRI, m_GFNeg(m_Reg(X))) &&
5259  mi_match(Y, MRI, m_GFNeg(m_Reg(Y)))) {
5260  // no opcode change
5261  } else
5262  return false;
5263 
5264  MatchInfo = [=, &MI](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
5265  Observer.changingInstr(MI);
5266  MI.setDesc(B.getTII().get(Opc));
5267  MI.getOperand(1).setReg(X);
5268  MI.getOperand(2).setReg(Y);
5269  Observer.changedInstr(MI);
5270  };
5271  return true;
5272 }
5273 
5274 bool CombinerHelper::matchFsubToFneg(MachineInstr &MI, Register &MatchInfo) {
5275  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_FSUB);
5276 
5277  Register LHS = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
5278  MatchInfo = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
5279  LLT Ty = MRI.getType(MI.getOperand(0).getReg());
5280 
5281  const auto LHSCst = Ty.isVector()
5282  ? getFConstantSplat(LHS, MRI, /* allowUndef */ true)
5283  : getFConstantVRegValWithLookThrough(LHS, MRI);
5284  if (!LHSCst)
5285  return false;
5286 
5287  // -0.0 is always allowed
5288  if (LHSCst->Value.isNegZero())
5289  return true;
5290 
5291  // +0.0 is only allowed if nsz is set.
5292  if (LHSCst->Value.isPosZero())
5293  return MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::FmNsz);
5294 
5295  return false;
5296 }

5306 /// Checks if \p MI is TargetOpcode::G_FMUL and contractable either
5307 /// due to global flags or MachineInstr flags.
5308 static bool isContractableFMul(MachineInstr &MI, bool AllowFusionGlobally) {
5309  if (MI.getOpcode() != TargetOpcode::G_FMUL)
5310  return false;
5311  return AllowFusionGlobally || MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::MIFlag::FmContract);

5314 static bool hasMoreUses(const MachineInstr &MI0, const MachineInstr &MI1,
5315  const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) {
5316  return std::distance(MRI.use_instr_nodbg_begin(MI0.getOperand(0).getReg()),
5317  MRI.use_instr_nodbg_end()) >
5318  std::distance(MRI.use_instr_nodbg_begin(MI1.getOperand(0).getReg()),
5319  MRI.use_instr_nodbg_end());
5320 }
5321 
5322 bool CombinerHelper::canCombineFMadOrFMA(MachineInstr &MI,
5323  bool &AllowFusionGlobally,
5324  bool &HasFMAD, bool &Aggressive,
5325  bool CanReassociate) {
5326 
5327  auto *MF = MI.getMF();
5328  const auto &TLI = *MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering();
5329  const TargetOptions &Options = MF->getTarget().Options;
5330  LLT DstType = MRI.getType(MI.getOperand(0).getReg());
5331 
5332  if (CanReassociate &&
5333  !(Options.UnsafeFPMath || MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::MIFlag::FmReassoc)))
5334  return false;
5335 
5336  // Floating-point multiply-add with intermediate rounding.
5337  HasFMAD = (!isPreLegalize() && TLI.isFMADLegal(MI, DstType));
5338  // Floating-point multiply-add without intermediate rounding.
5339  bool HasFMA = TLI.isFMAFasterThanFMulAndFAdd(*MF, DstType) &&
5340  isLegalOrBeforeLegalizer({TargetOpcode::G_FMA, {DstType}});
5341  // No valid opcode, do not combine.
5342  if (!HasFMAD && !HasFMA)
5343  return false;
5344 
5345  AllowFusionGlobally = Options.AllowFPOpFusion == FPOpFusion::Fast ||
5346  Options.UnsafeFPMath || HasFMAD;
5347  // If the addition is not contractable, do not combine.
5348  if (!AllowFusionGlobally && !MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::MIFlag::FmContract))
5349  return false;
5350 
5351  Aggressive = TLI.enableAggressiveFMAFusion(DstType);
5352  return true;
5353 }
5354 
5355 bool CombinerHelper::matchCombineFAddFMulToFMadOrFMA(
5356  MachineInstr &MI, std::function<void(MachineIRBuilder &)> &MatchInfo) {
5357  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_FADD);
5358 
5359  bool AllowFusionGlobally, HasFMAD, Aggressive;
5360  if (!canCombineFMadOrFMA(MI, AllowFusionGlobally, HasFMAD, Aggressive))
5361  return false;
5362 
5363  Register Op1 = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
5364  Register Op2 = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
5365  DefinitionAndSourceRegister LHS = {MRI.getVRegDef(Op1), Op1};
5366  DefinitionAndSourceRegister RHS = {MRI.getVRegDef(Op2), Op2};
5367  unsigned PreferredFusedOpcode =
5368  HasFMAD ? TargetOpcode::G_FMAD : TargetOpcode::G_FMA;
5369 
5370  // If we have two choices trying to fold (fadd (fmul u, v), (fmul x, y)),
5371  // prefer to fold the multiply with fewer uses.
5372  if (Aggressive && isContractableFMul(*LHS.MI, AllowFusionGlobally) &&
5373  isContractableFMul(*RHS.MI, AllowFusionGlobally)) {
5374  if (hasMoreUses(*LHS.MI, *RHS.MI, MRI))
5375  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
5376  }
5377 
5378  // fold (fadd (fmul x, y), z) -> (fma x, y, z)
5379  if (isContractableFMul(*LHS.MI, AllowFusionGlobally) &&
5380  (Aggressive || MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(LHS.Reg))) {
5381  MatchInfo = [=, &MI](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
5382  B.buildInstr(PreferredFusedOpcode, {MI.getOperand(0).getReg()},
5383  {LHS.MI->getOperand(1).getReg(),
5384  LHS.MI->getOperand(2).getReg(), RHS.Reg});
5385  };
5386  return true;
5387  }
5388 
5389  // fold (fadd x, (fmul y, z)) -> (fma y, z, x)
5390  if (isContractableFMul(*RHS.MI, AllowFusionGlobally) &&
5391  (Aggressive || MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(RHS.Reg))) {
5392  MatchInfo = [=, &MI](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
5393  B.buildInstr(PreferredFusedOpcode, {MI.getOperand(0).getReg()},
5394  {RHS.MI->getOperand(1).getReg(),
5395  RHS.MI->getOperand(2).getReg(), LHS.Reg});
5396  };
5397  return true;
5398  }
5399 
5400  return false;
5401 }
5402 
5403 bool CombinerHelper::matchCombineFAddFpExtFMulToFMadOrFMA(
5404  MachineInstr &MI, std::function<void(MachineIRBuilder &)> &MatchInfo) {
5405  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_FADD);
5406 
5407  bool AllowFusionGlobally, HasFMAD, Aggressive;
5408  if (!canCombineFMadOrFMA(MI, AllowFusionGlobally, HasFMAD, Aggressive))
5409  return false;
5410 
5411  const auto &TLI = *MI.getMF()->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering();
5412  Register Op1 = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
5413  Register Op2 = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
5414  DefinitionAndSourceRegister LHS = {MRI.getVRegDef(Op1), Op1};
5415  DefinitionAndSourceRegister RHS = {MRI.getVRegDef(Op2), Op2};
5416  LLT DstType = MRI.getType(MI.getOperand(0).getReg());
5417 
5418  unsigned PreferredFusedOpcode =
5419  HasFMAD ? TargetOpcode::G_FMAD : TargetOpcode::G_FMA;
5420 
5421  // If we have two choices trying to fold (fadd (fmul u, v), (fmul x, y)),
5422  // prefer to fold the multiply with fewer uses.
5423  if (Aggressive && isContractableFMul(*LHS.MI, AllowFusionGlobally) &&
5424  isContractableFMul(*RHS.MI, AllowFusionGlobally)) {
5425  if (hasMoreUses(*LHS.MI, *RHS.MI, MRI))
5426  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
5427  }
5428 
5429  // fold (fadd (fpext (fmul x, y)), z) -> (fma (fpext x), (fpext y), z)
5430  MachineInstr *FpExtSrc;
5431  if (mi_match(LHS.Reg, MRI, m_GFPExt(m_MInstr(FpExtSrc))) &&
5432  isContractableFMul(*FpExtSrc, AllowFusionGlobally) &&
5433  TLI.isFPExtFoldable(MI, PreferredFusedOpcode, DstType,
5434  MRI.getType(FpExtSrc->getOperand(1).getReg()))) {
5435  MatchInfo = [=, &MI](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
5436  auto FpExtX = B.buildFPExt(DstType, FpExtSrc->getOperand(1).getReg());
5437  auto FpExtY = B.buildFPExt(DstType, FpExtSrc->getOperand(2).getReg());
5438  B.buildInstr(PreferredFusedOpcode, {MI.getOperand(0).getReg()},
5439  {FpExtX.getReg(0), FpExtY.getReg(0), RHS.Reg});
5440  };
5441  return true;
5442  }
5443 
5444  // fold (fadd z, (fpext (fmul x, y))) -> (fma (fpext x), (fpext y), z)
5445  // Note: Commutes FADD operands.
5446  if (mi_match(RHS.Reg, MRI, m_GFPExt(m_MInstr(FpExtSrc))) &&
5447  isContractableFMul(*FpExtSrc, AllowFusionGlobally) &&
5448  TLI.isFPExtFoldable(MI, PreferredFusedOpcode, DstType,
5449  MRI.getType(FpExtSrc->getOperand(1).getReg()))) {
5450  MatchInfo = [=, &MI](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
5451  auto FpExtX = B.buildFPExt(DstType, FpExtSrc->getOperand(1).getReg());
5452  auto FpExtY = B.buildFPExt(DstType, FpExtSrc->getOperand(2).getReg());
5453  B.buildInstr(PreferredFusedOpcode, {MI.getOperand(0).getReg()},
5454  {FpExtX.getReg(0), FpExtY.getReg(0), LHS.Reg});
5455  };
5456  return true;
5457  }
5458 
5459  return false;
5460 }
5461 
5462 bool CombinerHelper::matchCombineFAddFMAFMulToFMadOrFMA(
5463  MachineInstr &MI, std::function<void(MachineIRBuilder &)> &MatchInfo) {
5464  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_FADD);
5465 
5466  bool AllowFusionGlobally, HasFMAD, Aggressive;
5467  if (!canCombineFMadOrFMA(MI, AllowFusionGlobally, HasFMAD, Aggressive, true))
5468  return false;
5469 
5470  Register Op1 = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
5471  Register Op2 = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
5472  DefinitionAndSourceRegister LHS = {MRI.getVRegDef(Op1), Op1};
5473  DefinitionAndSourceRegister RHS = {MRI.getVRegDef(Op2), Op2};
5474  LLT DstTy = MRI.getType(MI.getOperand(0).getReg());
5475 
5476  unsigned PreferredFusedOpcode =
5477  HasFMAD ? TargetOpcode::G_FMAD : TargetOpcode::G_FMA;
5478 
5479  // If we have two choices trying to fold (fadd (fmul u, v), (fmul x, y)),
5480  // prefer to fold the multiply with fewer uses.
5481  if (Aggressive && isContractableFMul(*LHS.MI, AllowFusionGlobally) &&
5482  isContractableFMul(*RHS.MI, AllowFusionGlobally)) {
5483  if (hasMoreUses(*LHS.MI, *RHS.MI, MRI))
5484  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
5485  }
5486 
5487  MachineInstr *FMA = nullptr;
5488  Register Z;
5489  // fold (fadd (fma x, y, (fmul u, v)), z) -> (fma x, y, (fma u, v, z))
5490  if (LHS.MI->getOpcode() == PreferredFusedOpcode &&
5491  (MRI.getVRegDef(LHS.MI->getOperand(3).getReg())->getOpcode() ==
5492  TargetOpcode::G_FMUL) &&
5493  MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(LHS.MI->getOperand(0).getReg()) &&
5494  MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(LHS.MI->getOperand(3).getReg())) {
5495  FMA = LHS.MI;
5496  Z = RHS.Reg;
5497  }
5498  // fold (fadd z, (fma x, y, (fmul u, v))) -> (fma x, y, (fma u, v, z))
5499  else if (RHS.MI->getOpcode() == PreferredFusedOpcode &&
5500  (MRI.getVRegDef(RHS.MI->getOperand(3).getReg())->getOpcode() ==
5501  TargetOpcode::G_FMUL) &&
5502  MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(RHS.MI->getOperand(0).getReg()) &&
5503  MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(RHS.MI->getOperand(3).getReg())) {
5504  Z = LHS.Reg;
5505  FMA = RHS.MI;
5506  }
5507 
5508  if (FMA) {
5509  MachineInstr *FMulMI = MRI.getVRegDef(FMA->getOperand(3).getReg());
5510  Register X = FMA->getOperand(1).getReg();
5511  Register Y = FMA->getOperand(2).getReg();
5512  Register U = FMulMI->getOperand(1).getReg();
5513  Register V = FMulMI->getOperand(2).getReg();
5514 
5515  MatchInfo = [=, &MI](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
5516  Register InnerFMA = MRI.createGenericVirtualRegister(DstTy);
5517  B.buildInstr(PreferredFusedOpcode, {InnerFMA}, {U, V, Z});
5518  B.buildInstr(PreferredFusedOpcode, {MI.getOperand(0).getReg()},
5519  {X, Y, InnerFMA});
5520  };
5521  return true;
5522  }
5523 
5524  return false;
5525 }
5526 
5527 bool CombinerHelper::matchCombineFAddFpExtFMulToFMadOrFMAAggressive(
5528  MachineInstr &MI, std::function<void(MachineIRBuilder &)> &MatchInfo) {
5529  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_FADD);
5530 
5531  bool AllowFusionGlobally, HasFMAD, Aggressive;
5532  if (!canCombineFMadOrFMA(MI, AllowFusionGlobally, HasFMAD, Aggressive))
5533  return false;
5534 
5535  if (!Aggressive)
5536  return false;
5537 
5538  const auto &TLI = *MI.getMF()->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering();
5539  LLT DstType = MRI.getType(MI.getOperand(0).getReg());
5540  Register Op1 = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
5541  Register Op2 = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
5542  DefinitionAndSourceRegister LHS = {MRI.getVRegDef(Op1), Op1};
5543  DefinitionAndSourceRegister RHS = {MRI.getVRegDef(Op2), Op2};
5544 
5545  unsigned PreferredFusedOpcode =
5546  HasFMAD ? TargetOpcode::G_FMAD : TargetOpcode::G_FMA;
5547 
5548  // If we have two choices trying to fold (fadd (fmul u, v), (fmul x, y)),
5549  // prefer to fold the multiply with fewer uses.
5550  if (Aggressive && isContractableFMul(*LHS.MI, AllowFusionGlobally) &&
5551  isContractableFMul(*RHS.MI, AllowFusionGlobally)) {
5552  if (hasMoreUses(*LHS.MI, *RHS.MI, MRI))
5553  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
5554  }
5555 
5556  // Builds: (fma x, y, (fma (fpext u), (fpext v), z))
5557  auto buildMatchInfo = [=, &MI](Register U, Register V, Register Z, Register X,
5558  Register Y, MachineIRBuilder &B) {
5559  Register FpExtU = B.buildFPExt(DstType, U).getReg(0);
5560  Register FpExtV = B.buildFPExt(DstType, V).getReg(0);
5561  Register InnerFMA =
5562  B.buildInstr(PreferredFusedOpcode, {DstType}, {FpExtU, FpExtV, Z})
5563  .getReg(0);
5564  B.buildInstr(PreferredFusedOpcode, {MI.getOperand(0).getReg()},
5565  {X, Y, InnerFMA});
5566  };
5567 
5568  MachineInstr *FMulMI, *FMAMI;
5569  // fold (fadd (fma x, y, (fpext (fmul u, v))), z)
5570  // -> (fma x, y, (fma (fpext u), (fpext v), z))
5571  if (LHS.MI->getOpcode() == PreferredFusedOpcode &&
5572  mi_match(LHS.MI->getOperand(3).getReg(), MRI,
5573  m_GFPExt(m_MInstr(FMulMI))) &&
5574  isContractableFMul(*FMulMI, AllowFusionGlobally) &&
5575  TLI.isFPExtFoldable(MI, PreferredFusedOpcode, DstType,
5576  MRI.getType(FMulMI->getOperand(0).getReg()))) {
5577  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
5578  buildMatchInfo(FMulMI->getOperand(1).getReg(),
5579  FMulMI->getOperand(2).getReg(), RHS.Reg,
5580  LHS.MI->getOperand(1).getReg(),
5581  LHS.MI->getOperand(2).getReg(), B);
5582  };
5583  return true;
5584  }
5585 
5586  // fold (fadd (fpext (fma x, y, (fmul u, v))), z)
5587  // -> (fma (fpext x), (fpext y), (fma (fpext u), (fpext v), z))
5588  // FIXME: This turns two single-precision and one double-precision
5589  // operation into two double-precision operations, which might not be
5590  // interesting for all targets, especially GPUs.
5591  if (mi_match(LHS.Reg, MRI, m_GFPExt(m_MInstr(FMAMI))) &&
5592  FMAMI->getOpcode() == PreferredFusedOpcode) {
5593  MachineInstr *FMulMI = MRI.getVRegDef(FMAMI->getOperand(3).getReg());
5594  if (isContractableFMul(*FMulMI, AllowFusionGlobally) &&
5595  TLI.isFPExtFoldable(MI, PreferredFusedOpcode, DstType,
5596  MRI.getType(FMAMI->getOperand(0).getReg()))) {
5597  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
5598  Register X = FMAMI->getOperand(1).getReg();
5599  Register Y = FMAMI->getOperand(2).getReg();
5600  X = B.buildFPExt(DstType, X).getReg(0);
5601  Y = B.buildFPExt(DstType, Y).getReg(0);
5602  buildMatchInfo(FMulMI->getOperand(1).getReg(),
5603  FMulMI->getOperand(2).getReg(), RHS.Reg, X, Y, B);
5604  };
5605 
5606  return true;
5607  }
5608  }
5609 
5610  // fold (fadd z, (fma x, y, (fpext (fmul u, v)))
5611  // -> (fma x, y, (fma (fpext u), (fpext v), z))
5612  if (RHS.MI->getOpcode() == PreferredFusedOpcode &&
5613  mi_match(RHS.MI->getOperand(3).getReg(), MRI,
5614  m_GFPExt(m_MInstr(FMulMI))) &&
5615  isContractableFMul(*FMulMI, AllowFusionGlobally) &&
5616  TLI.isFPExtFoldable(MI, PreferredFusedOpcode, DstType,
5617  MRI.getType(FMulMI->getOperand(0).getReg()))) {
5618  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
5619  buildMatchInfo(FMulMI->getOperand(1).getReg(),
5620  FMulMI->getOperand(2).getReg(), LHS.Reg,
5621  RHS.MI->getOperand(1).getReg(),
5622  RHS.MI->getOperand(2).getReg(), B);
5623  };
5624  return true;
5625  }
5626 
5627  // fold (fadd z, (fpext (fma x, y, (fmul u, v)))
5628  // -> (fma (fpext x), (fpext y), (fma (fpext u), (fpext v), z))
5629  // FIXME: This turns two single-precision and one double-precision
5630  // operation into two double-precision operations, which might not be
5631  // interesting for all targets, especially GPUs.
5632  if (mi_match(RHS.Reg, MRI, m_GFPExt(m_MInstr(FMAMI))) &&
5633  FMAMI->getOpcode() == PreferredFusedOpcode) {
5634  MachineInstr *FMulMI = MRI.getVRegDef(FMAMI->getOperand(3).getReg());
5635  if (isContractableFMul(*FMulMI, AllowFusionGlobally) &&
5636  TLI.isFPExtFoldable(MI, PreferredFusedOpcode, DstType,
5637  MRI.getType(FMAMI->getOperand(0).getReg()))) {
5638  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
5639  Register X = FMAMI->getOperand(1).getReg();
5640  Register Y = FMAMI->getOperand(2).getReg();
5641  X = B.buildFPExt(DstType, X).getReg(0);
5642  Y = B.buildFPExt(DstType, Y).getReg(0);
5643  buildMatchInfo(FMulMI->getOperand(1).getReg(),
5644  FMulMI->getOperand(2).getReg(), LHS.Reg, X, Y, B);
5645  };
5646  return true;
5647  }
5648  }
5649 
5650  return false;
5651 }
5652 
5653 bool CombinerHelper::matchCombineFSubFMulToFMadOrFMA(
5654  MachineInstr &MI, std::function<void(MachineIRBuilder &)> &MatchInfo) {
5655  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_FSUB);
5656 
5657  bool AllowFusionGlobally, HasFMAD, Aggressive;
5658  if (!canCombineFMadOrFMA(MI, AllowFusionGlobally, HasFMAD, Aggressive))
5659  return false;
5660 
5661  Register Op1 = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
5662  Register Op2 = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
5663  DefinitionAndSourceRegister LHS = {MRI.getVRegDef(Op1), Op1};
5664  DefinitionAndSourceRegister RHS = {MRI.getVRegDef(Op2), Op2};
5665  LLT DstTy = MRI.getType(MI.getOperand(0).getReg());
5666 
5667  // If we have two choices trying to fold (fadd (fmul u, v), (fmul x, y)),
5668  // prefer to fold the multiply with fewer uses.
5669  int FirstMulHasFewerUses = true;
5670  if (isContractableFMul(*LHS.MI, AllowFusionGlobally) &&
5671  isContractableFMul(*RHS.MI, AllowFusionGlobally) &&
5672  hasMoreUses(*LHS.MI, *RHS.MI, MRI))
5673  FirstMulHasFewerUses = false;
5674 
5675  unsigned PreferredFusedOpcode =
5676  HasFMAD ? TargetOpcode::G_FMAD : TargetOpcode::G_FMA;
5677 
5678  // fold (fsub (fmul x, y), z) -> (fma x, y, -z)
5679  if (FirstMulHasFewerUses &&
5680  (isContractableFMul(*LHS.MI, AllowFusionGlobally) &&
5681  (Aggressive || MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(LHS.Reg)))) {
5682  MatchInfo = [=, &MI](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
5683  Register NegZ = B.buildFNeg(DstTy, RHS.Reg).getReg(0);
5684  B.buildInstr(PreferredFusedOpcode, {MI.getOperand(0).getReg()},
5685  {LHS.MI->getOperand(1).getReg(),
5686  LHS.MI->getOperand(2).getReg(), NegZ});
5687  };
5688  return true;
5689  }
5690  // fold (fsub x, (fmul y, z)) -> (fma -y, z, x)
5691  else if ((isContractableFMul(*RHS.MI, AllowFusionGlobally) &&
5692  (Aggressive || MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(RHS.Reg)))) {
5693  MatchInfo = [=, &MI](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
5694  Register NegY =
5695  B.buildFNeg(DstTy, RHS.MI->getOperand(1).getReg()).getReg(0);
5696  B.buildInstr(PreferredFusedOpcode, {MI.getOperand(0).getReg()},
5697  {NegY, RHS.MI->getOperand(2).getReg(), LHS.Reg});
5698  };
5699  return true;
5700  }
5701 
5702  return false;
5703 }

5705 bool CombinerHelper::matchCombineFSubFNegFMulToFMadOrFMA(
5706  MachineInstr &MI, std::function<void(MachineIRBuilder &)> &MatchInfo) {
5707  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_FSUB);
5708 
5709  bool AllowFusionGlobally, HasFMAD, Aggressive;
5710  if (!canCombineFMadOrFMA(MI, AllowFusionGlobally, HasFMAD, Aggressive))
5711  return false;
5712 
5713  Register LHSReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
5714  Register RHSReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
5715  LLT DstTy = MRI.getType(MI.getOperand(0).getReg());
5716 
5717  unsigned PreferredFusedOpcode =
5718  HasFMAD ? TargetOpcode::G_FMAD : TargetOpcode::G_FMA;
5719 
5720  MachineInstr *FMulMI;
5721  // fold (fsub (fneg (fmul x, y)), z) -> (fma (fneg x), y, (fneg z))
5722  if (mi_match(LHSReg, MRI, m_GFNeg(m_MInstr(FMulMI))) &&
5723  (Aggressive || (MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(LHSReg) &&
5724  MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(FMulMI->getOperand(0).getReg()))) &&
5725  isContractableFMul(*FMulMI, AllowFusionGlobally)) {

5727  Register NegX =
5728  B.buildFNeg(DstTy, FMulMI->getOperand(1).getReg()).getReg(0);
5729  Register NegZ = B.buildFNeg(DstTy, RHSReg).getReg(0);
5730  B.buildInstr(PreferredFusedOpcode, {MI.getOperand(0).getReg()},
5731  {NegX, FMulMI->getOperand(2).getReg(), NegZ});
5732  };
5733  return true;
5734  }
5735 
5736  // fold (fsub x, (fneg (fmul, y, z))) -> (fma y, z, x)
5737  if (mi_match(RHSReg, MRI, m_GFNeg(m_MInstr(FMulMI))) &&
5738  (Aggressive || (MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(RHSReg) &&
5739  MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(FMulMI->getOperand(0).getReg()))) &&
5740  isContractableFMul(*FMulMI, AllowFusionGlobally)) {
5741  MatchInfo = [=, &MI](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
5742  B.buildInstr(PreferredFusedOpcode, {MI.getOperand(0).getReg()},
5743  {FMulMI->getOperand(1).getReg(),
5744  FMulMI->getOperand(2).getReg(), LHSReg});
5745  };
5746  return true;
5747  }
5748 
5749  return false;
5750 }
5751 
5752 bool CombinerHelper::matchCombineFSubFpExtFMulToFMadOrFMA(
5753  MachineInstr &MI, std::function<void(MachineIRBuilder &)> &MatchInfo) {
5754  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_FSUB);
5755 
5756  bool AllowFusionGlobally, HasFMAD, Aggressive;
5757  if (!canCombineFMadOrFMA(MI, AllowFusionGlobally, HasFMAD, Aggressive))
5758  return false;
5759 
5760  Register LHSReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
5761  Register RHSReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
5762  LLT DstTy = MRI.getType(MI.getOperand(0).getReg());
5763 
5764  unsigned PreferredFusedOpcode =
5765  HasFMAD ? TargetOpcode::G_FMAD : TargetOpcode::G_FMA;
5766 
5767  MachineInstr *FMulMI;
5768  // fold (fsub (fpext (fmul x, y)), z) -> (fma (fpext x), (fpext y), (fneg z))
5769  if (mi_match(LHSReg, MRI, m_GFPExt(m_MInstr(FMulMI))) &&
5770  isContractableFMul(*FMulMI, AllowFusionGlobally) &&
5771  (Aggressive || MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(LHSReg))) {
5772  MatchInfo = [=, &MI](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
5773  Register FpExtX =
5774  B.buildFPExt(DstTy, FMulMI->getOperand(1).getReg()).getReg(0);
5775  Register FpExtY =
5776  B.buildFPExt(DstTy, FMulMI->getOperand(2).getReg()).getReg(0);
5777  Register NegZ = B.buildFNeg(DstTy, RHSReg).getReg(0);
5778  B.buildInstr(PreferredFusedOpcode, {MI.getOperand(0).getReg()},
5779  {FpExtX, FpExtY, NegZ});
5780  };
5781  return true;
5782  }
5783 
5784  // fold (fsub x, (fpext (fmul y, z))) -> (fma (fneg (fpext y)), (fpext z), x)
5785  if (mi_match(RHSReg, MRI, m_GFPExt(m_MInstr(FMulMI))) &&
5786  isContractableFMul(*FMulMI, AllowFusionGlobally) &&
5787  (Aggressive || MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(RHSReg))) {
5788  MatchInfo = [=, &MI](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
5789  Register FpExtY =
5790  B.buildFPExt(DstTy, FMulMI->getOperand(1).getReg()).getReg(0);
5791  Register NegY = B.buildFNeg(DstTy, FpExtY).getReg(0);
5792  Register FpExtZ =
5793  B.buildFPExt(DstTy, FMulMI->getOperand(2).getReg()).getReg(0);
5794  B.buildInstr(PreferredFusedOpcode, {MI.getOperand(0).getReg()},
5795  {NegY, FpExtZ, LHSReg});
5796  };
5797  return true;
5798  }
5799 
5800  return false;
5801 }
5802 
5803 bool CombinerHelper::matchCombineFSubFpExtFNegFMulToFMadOrFMA(
5804  MachineInstr &MI, std::function<void(MachineIRBuilder &)> &MatchInfo) {
5805  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_FSUB);
5806 
5807  bool AllowFusionGlobally, HasFMAD, Aggressive;
5808  if (!canCombineFMadOrFMA(MI, AllowFusionGlobally, HasFMAD, Aggressive))
5809  return false;
5810 
5811  const auto &TLI = *MI.getMF()->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering();
5812  LLT DstTy = MRI.getType(MI.getOperand(0).getReg());
5813  Register LHSReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
5814  Register RHSReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
5815 
5816  unsigned PreferredFusedOpcode =
5817  HasFMAD ? TargetOpcode::G_FMAD : TargetOpcode::G_FMA;
5818 
5819  auto buildMatchInfo = [=](Register Dst, Register X, Register Y, Register Z,
5820  MachineIRBuilder &B) {
5821  Register FpExtX = B.buildFPExt(DstTy, X).getReg(0);
5822  Register FpExtY = B.buildFPExt(DstTy, Y).getReg(0);
5823  B.buildInstr(PreferredFusedOpcode, {Dst}, {FpExtX, FpExtY, Z});
5824  };
5825 
5826  MachineInstr *FMulMI;
5827  // fold (fsub (fpext (fneg (fmul x, y))), z) ->
5828  // (fneg (fma (fpext x), (fpext y), z))
5829  // fold (fsub (fneg (fpext (fmul x, y))), z) ->
5830  // (fneg (fma (fpext x), (fpext y), z))
5831  if ((mi_match(LHSReg, MRI, m_GFPExt(m_GFNeg(m_MInstr(FMulMI)))) ||
5832  mi_match(LHSReg, MRI, m_GFNeg(m_GFPExt(m_MInstr(FMulMI))))) &&
5833  isContractableFMul(*FMulMI, AllowFusionGlobally) &&
5834  TLI.isFPExtFoldable(MI, PreferredFusedOpcode, DstTy,
5835  MRI.getType(FMulMI->getOperand(0).getReg()))) {
5836  MatchInfo = [=, &MI](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
5837  Register FMAReg = MRI.createGenericVirtualRegister(DstTy);
5838  buildMatchInfo(FMAReg, FMulMI->getOperand(1).getReg(),
5839  FMulMI->getOperand(2).getReg(), RHSReg, B);
5840  B.buildFNeg(MI.getOperand(0).getReg(), FMAReg);
5841  };
5842  return true;
5843  }
5844 
5845  // fold (fsub x, (fpext (fneg (fmul y, z)))) -> (fma (fpext y), (fpext z), x)
5846  // fold (fsub x, (fneg (fpext (fmul y, z)))) -> (fma (fpext y), (fpext z), x)
5847  if ((mi_match(RHSReg, MRI, m_GFPExt(m_GFNeg(m_MInstr(FMulMI)))) ||
5848  mi_match(RHSReg, MRI, m_GFNeg(m_GFPExt(m_MInstr(FMulMI))))) &&
5849  isContractableFMul(*FMulMI, AllowFusionGlobally) &&
5850  TLI.isFPExtFoldable(MI, PreferredFusedOpcode, DstTy,
5851  MRI.getType(FMulMI->getOperand(0).getReg()))) {
5852  MatchInfo = [=, &MI](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
5853  buildMatchInfo(MI.getOperand(0).getReg(), FMulMI->getOperand(1).getReg(),
5854  FMulMI->getOperand(2).getReg(), LHSReg, B);
5855  };
5856  return true;
5857  }
5858 
5859  return false;
5860 }
5861 
5862 bool CombinerHelper::matchSelectToLogical(MachineInstr &MI,
5863  BuildFnTy &MatchInfo) {
5864  GSelect &Sel = cast<GSelect>(MI);
5865  Register DstReg = Sel.getReg(0);
5866  Register Cond = Sel.getCondReg();
5867  Register TrueReg = Sel.getTrueReg();
5868  Register FalseReg = Sel.getFalseReg();
5869 
5870  auto *TrueDef = getDefIgnoringCopies(TrueReg, MRI);
5871  auto *FalseDef = getDefIgnoringCopies(FalseReg, MRI);
5872 
5873  const LLT CondTy = MRI.getType(Cond);
5874  const LLT OpTy = MRI.getType(TrueReg);
5875  if (CondTy != OpTy || OpTy.getScalarSizeInBits() != 1)
5876  return false;
5877 
5878  // We have a boolean select.
5879 
5880  // select Cond, Cond, F --> or Cond, F
5881  // select Cond, 1, F --> or Cond, F
5882  auto MaybeCstTrue = isConstantOrConstantSplatVector(*TrueDef, MRI);
5883  if (Cond == TrueReg || (MaybeCstTrue && MaybeCstTrue->isOne())) {
5884  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &MIB) {
5885  MIB.buildOr(DstReg, Cond, FalseReg);
5886  };
5887  return true;
5888  }
5889 
5890  // select Cond, T, Cond --> and Cond, T
5891  // select Cond, T, 0 --> and Cond, T
5892  auto MaybeCstFalse = isConstantOrConstantSplatVector(*FalseDef, MRI);
5893  if (Cond == FalseReg || (MaybeCstFalse && MaybeCstFalse->isZero())) {
5894  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &MIB) {
5895  MIB.buildAnd(DstReg, Cond, TrueReg);
5896  };
5897  return true;
5898  }
5899 
5900  // select Cond, T, 1 --> or (not Cond), T
5901  if (MaybeCstFalse && MaybeCstFalse->isOne()) {
5902  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &MIB) {
5903  MIB.buildOr(DstReg, MIB.buildNot(OpTy, Cond), TrueReg);
5904  };
5905  return true;
5906  }
5907 
5908  // select Cond, 0, F --> and (not Cond), F
5909  if (MaybeCstTrue && MaybeCstTrue->isZero()) {
5910  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &MIB) {
5911  MIB.buildAnd(DstReg, MIB.buildNot(OpTy, Cond), FalseReg);
5912  };
5913  return true;
5914  }
5915  return false;
5916 }
5917 
5918 bool CombinerHelper::matchCombineFMinMaxNaN(MachineInstr &MI,
5919  unsigned &IdxToPropagate) {
5920  bool PropagateNaN;
5921  switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
5922  default:
5923  return false;
5924  case TargetOpcode::G_FMINNUM:
5925  case TargetOpcode::G_FMAXNUM:
5926  PropagateNaN = false;
5927  break;
5928  case TargetOpcode::G_FMINIMUM:
5929  case TargetOpcode::G_FMAXIMUM:
5930  PropagateNaN = true;
5931  break;
5932  }
5933 
5934  auto MatchNaN = [&](unsigned Idx) {
5935  Register MaybeNaNReg = MI.getOperand(Idx).getReg();
5936  const ConstantFP *MaybeCst = getConstantFPVRegVal(MaybeNaNReg, MRI);
5937  if (!MaybeCst || !MaybeCst->getValueAPF().isNaN())
5938  return false;
5939  IdxToPropagate = PropagateNaN ? Idx : (Idx == 1 ? 2 : 1);
5940  return true;
5941  };
5942 
5943  return MatchNaN(1) || MatchNaN(2);
5944 }

5946 bool CombinerHelper::matchAddSubSameReg(MachineInstr &MI, Register &Src) {
5947  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_ADD && "Expected a G_ADD");
5948  Register LHS = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
5949  Register RHS = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
5950 
5951  // Helper lambda to check for opportunities for
5952  // A + (B - A) -> B
5953  // (B - A) + A -> B
5954  auto CheckFold = [&](Register MaybeSub, Register MaybeSameReg) {
5955  Register Reg;
5956  return mi_match(MaybeSub, MRI, m_GSub(m_Reg(Src), m_Reg(Reg))) &&
5957  Reg == MaybeSameReg;
5958  };
5959  return CheckFold(LHS, RHS) || CheckFold(RHS, LHS);
5960 }

5962 bool CombinerHelper::matchBuildVectorIdentityFold(MachineInstr &MI,
5963  Register &MatchInfo) {
5964  // This combine folds the following patterns:
5965  //
5966  // G_BUILD_VECTOR_TRUNC (G_BITCAST(x), G_LSHR(G_BITCAST(x), k))
5967  // G_BUILD_VECTOR(G_TRUNC(G_BITCAST(x)), G_TRUNC(G_LSHR(G_BITCAST(x), k)))
5968  // into
5969  // x
5970  // if
5971  // k == sizeof(VecEltTy)/2
5972  // type(x) == type(dst)
5973  //
5974  // G_BUILD_VECTOR(G_TRUNC(G_BITCAST(x)), undef)
5975  // into
5976  // x
5977  // if
5978  // type(x) == type(dst)
5979 
5980  LLT DstVecTy = MRI.getType(MI.getOperand(0).getReg());
5981  LLT DstEltTy = DstVecTy.getElementType();
5982 
5983  Register Lo, Hi;
5984 
5985  if (mi_match(
5986  MI, MRI,
5987  m_GBuildVector(m_GTrunc(m_GBitcast(m_Reg(Lo))), m_GImplicitDef()))) {
5988  MatchInfo = Lo;
5989  return MRI.getType(MatchInfo) == DstVecTy;
5990  }
5991 
5992  std::optional<ValueAndVReg> ShiftAmount;
5993  const auto LoPattern = m_GBitcast(m_Reg(Lo));
5994  const auto HiPattern = m_GLShr(m_GBitcast(m_Reg(Hi)), m_GCst(ShiftAmount));
5995  if (mi_match(
5996  MI, MRI,
5997  m_any_of(m_GBuildVectorTrunc(LoPattern, HiPattern),
5998  m_GBuildVector(m_GTrunc(LoPattern), m_GTrunc(HiPattern))))) {
5999  if (Lo == Hi && ShiftAmount->Value == DstEltTy.getSizeInBits()) {
6000  MatchInfo = Lo;
6001  return MRI.getType(MatchInfo) == DstVecTy;
6002  }
6003  }
6004 
6005  return false;
6006 }
6007 
6008 bool CombinerHelper::matchTruncBuildVectorFold(MachineInstr &MI,
6009  Register &MatchInfo) {
6010  // Replace (G_TRUNC (G_BITCAST (G_BUILD_VECTOR x, y)) with just x
6011  // if type(x) == type(G_TRUNC)
6012  if (!mi_match(MI.getOperand(1).getReg(), MRI,
6013  m_GBitcast(m_GBuildVector(m_Reg(MatchInfo), m_Reg()))))
6014  return false;
6015 
6016  return MRI.getType(MatchInfo) == MRI.getType(MI.getOperand(0).getReg());
6017 }
6018 
6019 bool CombinerHelper::matchTruncLshrBuildVectorFold(MachineInstr &MI,
6020  Register &MatchInfo) {
6021  // Replace (G_TRUNC (G_LSHR (G_BITCAST (G_BUILD_VECTOR x, y)), K)) with
6022  // y if K == size of vector element type
6023  std::optional<ValueAndVReg> ShiftAmt;
6024  if (!mi_match(MI.getOperand(1).getReg(), MRI,
6025  m_GLShr(m_GBitcast(m_GBuildVector(m_Reg(), m_Reg(MatchInfo))),
6026  m_GCst(ShiftAmt))))
6027  return false;
6028 
6029  LLT MatchTy = MRI.getType(MatchInfo);
6030  return ShiftAmt->Value.getZExtValue() == MatchTy.getSizeInBits() &&
6031  MatchTy == MRI.getType(MI.getOperand(0).getReg());
6032 }
6033 
6034 unsigned CombinerHelper::getFPMinMaxOpcForSelect(
6035  CmpInst::Predicate Pred, LLT DstTy,
6036  SelectPatternNaNBehaviour VsNaNRetVal) const {
6037  assert(VsNaNRetVal != SelectPatternNaNBehaviour::NOT_APPLICABLE &&
6038  "Expected a NaN behaviour?");
6039  // Choose an opcode based off of legality or the behaviour when one of the
6040  // LHS/RHS may be NaN.
6041  switch (Pred) {
6042  default:
6043  return 0;
6044  case CmpInst::FCMP_UGT:
6045  case CmpInst::FCMP_UGE:
6046  case CmpInst::FCMP_OGT:
6047  case CmpInst::FCMP_OGE:
6048  if (VsNaNRetVal == SelectPatternNaNBehaviour::RETURNS_OTHER)
6049  return TargetOpcode::G_FMAXNUM;
6050  if (VsNaNRetVal == SelectPatternNaNBehaviour::RETURNS_NAN)
6051  return TargetOpcode::G_FMAXIMUM;
6052  if (isLegal({TargetOpcode::G_FMAXNUM, {DstTy}}))
6053  return TargetOpcode::G_FMAXNUM;
6054  if (isLegal({TargetOpcode::G_FMAXIMUM, {DstTy}}))
6055  return TargetOpcode::G_FMAXIMUM;
6056  return 0;
6057  case CmpInst::FCMP_ULT:
6058  case CmpInst::FCMP_ULE:
6059  case CmpInst::FCMP_OLT:
6060  case CmpInst::FCMP_OLE:
6061  if (VsNaNRetVal == SelectPatternNaNBehaviour::RETURNS_OTHER)
6062  return TargetOpcode::G_FMINNUM;
6063  if (VsNaNRetVal == SelectPatternNaNBehaviour::RETURNS_NAN)
6064  return TargetOpcode::G_FMINIMUM;
6065  if (isLegal({TargetOpcode::G_FMINNUM, {DstTy}}))
6066  return TargetOpcode::G_FMINNUM;
6067  if (!isLegal({TargetOpcode::G_FMINIMUM, {DstTy}}))
6068  return 0;
6069  return TargetOpcode::G_FMINIMUM;
6070  }
6071 }
6072 
6073 CombinerHelper::SelectPatternNaNBehaviour
6074 CombinerHelper::computeRetValAgainstNaN(Register LHS, Register RHS,
6075  bool IsOrderedComparison) const {
6076  bool LHSSafe = isKnownNeverNaN(LHS, MRI);
6077  bool RHSSafe = isKnownNeverNaN(RHS, MRI);
6078  // Completely unsafe.
6079  if (!LHSSafe && !RHSSafe)
6080  return SelectPatternNaNBehaviour::NOT_APPLICABLE;
6081  if (LHSSafe && RHSSafe)
6082  return SelectPatternNaNBehaviour::RETURNS_ANY;
6083  // An ordered comparison will return false when given a NaN, so it
6084  // returns the RHS.
6085  if (IsOrderedComparison)
6086  return LHSSafe ? SelectPatternNaNBehaviour::RETURNS_NAN
6087  : SelectPatternNaNBehaviour::RETURNS_OTHER;
6088  // An unordered comparison will return true when given a NaN, so it
6089  // returns the LHS.
6090  return LHSSafe ? SelectPatternNaNBehaviour::RETURNS_OTHER
6091  : SelectPatternNaNBehaviour::RETURNS_NAN;
6092 }
6093 
6094 bool CombinerHelper::matchFPSelectToMinMax(Register Dst, Register Cond,
6095  Register TrueVal, Register FalseVal,
6096  BuildFnTy &MatchInfo) {
6097  // Match: select (fcmp cond x, y) x, y
6098  // select (fcmp cond x, y) y, x
6099  // And turn it into fminnum/fmaxnum or fmin/fmax based off of the condition.
6100  LLT DstTy = MRI.getType(Dst);
6101  // Bail out early on pointers, since we'll never want to fold to a min/max.
6102  if (DstTy.isPointer())
6103  return false;
6104  // Match a floating point compare with a less-than/greater-than predicate.
6105  // TODO: Allow multiple users of the compare if they are all selects.
6106  CmpInst::Predicate Pred;
6107  Register CmpLHS, CmpRHS;
6108  if (!mi_match(Cond, MRI,
6109  m_OneNonDBGUse(
6110  m_GFCmp(m_Pred(Pred), m_Reg(CmpLHS), m_Reg(CmpRHS)))) ||
6111  CmpInst::isEquality(Pred))
6112  return false;
6113  SelectPatternNaNBehaviour ResWithKnownNaNInfo =
6114  computeRetValAgainstNaN(CmpLHS, CmpRHS, CmpInst::isOrdered(Pred));
6115  if (ResWithKnownNaNInfo == SelectPatternNaNBehaviour::NOT_APPLICABLE)
6116  return false;
6117  if (TrueVal == CmpRHS && FalseVal == CmpLHS) {
6118  std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
6119  Pred = CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
6120  if (ResWithKnownNaNInfo == SelectPatternNaNBehaviour::RETURNS_NAN)
6121  ResWithKnownNaNInfo = SelectPatternNaNBehaviour::RETURNS_OTHER;
6122  else if (ResWithKnownNaNInfo == SelectPatternNaNBehaviour::RETURNS_OTHER)
6123  ResWithKnownNaNInfo = SelectPatternNaNBehaviour::RETURNS_NAN;
6124  }
6125  if (TrueVal != CmpLHS || FalseVal != CmpRHS)
6126  return false;
6127  // Decide what type of max/min this should be based off of the predicate.
6128  unsigned Opc = getFPMinMaxOpcForSelect(Pred, DstTy, ResWithKnownNaNInfo);
6129  if (!Opc || !isLegal({Opc, {DstTy}}))
6130  return false;
6131  // Comparisons between signed zero and zero may have different results...
6132  // unless we have fmaximum/fminimum. In that case, we know -0 < 0.
6133  if (Opc != TargetOpcode::G_FMAXIMUM && Opc != TargetOpcode::G_FMINIMUM) {
6134  // We don't know if a comparison between two 0s will give us a consistent
6135  // result. Be conservative and only proceed if at least one side is
6136  // non-zero.
6137  auto KnownNonZeroSide = getFConstantVRegValWithLookThrough(CmpLHS, MRI);
6138  if (!KnownNonZeroSide || !KnownNonZeroSide->Value.isNonZero()) {
6139  KnownNonZeroSide = getFConstantVRegValWithLookThrough(CmpRHS, MRI);
6140  if (!KnownNonZeroSide || !KnownNonZeroSide->Value.isNonZero())
6141  return false;
6142  }
6143  }
6144  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
6145  B.buildInstr(Opc, {Dst}, {CmpLHS, CmpRHS});
6146  };
6147  return true;
6148 }
6149 
6150 bool CombinerHelper::matchSimplifySelectToMinMax(MachineInstr &MI,
6151  BuildFnTy &MatchInfo) {
6152  // TODO: Handle integer cases.
6153  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_SELECT);
6154  // Condition may be fed by a truncated compare.
6155  Register Cond = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
6156  Register MaybeTrunc;
6157  if (mi_match(Cond, MRI, m_OneNonDBGUse(m_GTrunc(m_Reg(MaybeTrunc)))))
6158  Cond = MaybeTrunc;
6159  Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
6160  Register TrueVal = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
6161  Register FalseVal = MI.getOperand(3).getReg();
6162  return matchFPSelectToMinMax(Dst, Cond, TrueVal, FalseVal, MatchInfo);
6163 }
6164 
6165 bool CombinerHelper::matchRedundantBinOpInEquality(MachineInstr &MI,
6166  BuildFnTy &MatchInfo) {
6167  assert(MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::G_ICMP);
6168  // (X + Y) == X --> Y == 0
6169  // (X + Y) != X --> Y != 0
6170  // (X - Y) == X --> Y == 0
6171  // (X - Y) != X --> Y != 0
6172  // (X ^ Y) == X --> Y == 0
6173  // (X ^ Y) != X --> Y != 0
6174  Register Dst = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
6175  CmpInst::Predicate Pred;
6176  Register X, Y, OpLHS, OpRHS;
6177  bool MatchedSub = mi_match(
6178  Dst, MRI,
6179  m_c_GICmp(m_Pred(Pred), m_Reg(X), m_GSub(m_Reg(OpLHS), m_Reg(Y))));
6180  if (MatchedSub && X != OpLHS)
6181  return false;
6182  if (!MatchedSub) {
6183  if (!mi_match(Dst, MRI,
6184  m_c_GICmp(m_Pred(Pred), m_Reg(X),
6185  m_any_of(m_GAdd(m_Reg(OpLHS), m_Reg(OpRHS)),
6186  m_GXor(m_Reg(OpLHS), m_Reg(OpRHS))))))
6187  return false;
6188  Y = X == OpLHS ? OpRHS : X == OpRHS ? OpLHS : Register();
6189  }
6190  MatchInfo = [=](MachineIRBuilder &B) {
6191  auto Zero = B.buildConstant(MRI.getType(Y), 0);
6192  B.buildICmp(Pred, Dst, Y, Zero);
6193  };
6194  return CmpInst::isEquality(Pred) && Y.isValid();
6195 }

6203  return true;
6204  return false;
